Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).', 'Wikipedia:Lipid "Lipids constitute a group of naturally occurring molecules that include fats, waxes, sterols, fat-soluble vitamins (such as vitamins A, D, E, and K), monoglycerides, diglycerides, triglycerides, phospholipids, and others. The main biological functions of lipids include energy storage, signaling, and acting as structural components of cell membranes. Lipids have found applications in cosmetic and food industries as well as in nanotechnology.']

name: Pyridines and derivatives
def: Compounds containing a pyridine ring, which is a six-member aromatic heterocycle which consists of one nitrogen atom and five carbon atoms." []

name: Pyrroles
def: Compounds containing a pyrrole ring, which is a five-member aromatic heterocycle with one nitrogen atom and four carbon atoms." []
xrefs: ['Wikipedia:Category\\:Pyrroles']

name: Pyrrolines
def: Compounds containing a pyrroline ring, which is a five-member unsaturated aliphatic ring with one nitrogen atom and four carbon atoms." []

name: Tetrazines
def: Organic compounds containing a tetrazine ring, which is a six-membered aromatic heterocycle made up of four nitrogen atoms and a two carbon atoms." []

name: Thiadiazoles
def: Cyclic organic compounds containing a thiadiazole ring, which is a five-membered aromatic heterocycle made up of one sulfur atom and two nitrogen atoms." []
synonyms: ['thiadiazoles" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38099]', 'Thiadiazoles" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D013830, MESH:D02.886.675.867, MESH:D03.383.129.708.867]']
xrefs: ['Wikipedia:Category\\:Thiadiazoles']

name: Thiazines
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing an aliphatic unsaturated six-member ring with four carbon atoms, one sulfur atom, and one nitrogen. Isomers include 1,2-thiazines, 1,3-thiazines, and 1,4-thiazines." []
synonyms: ['thiazine" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38326]', 'Thiazines" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D013843, MESH:D02.886.665, MESH:D03.383.855]']

name: Thiazoles
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a five-member aromatic ring made up of one sulfur atom, one nitrogen, and three carbon atoms." []
synonyms: ['thiazoles" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:48901]', 'Thiazoles" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D013844, MESH:D02.886.675, MESH:D03.383.129.708]']

name: Thiepins
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing an unsaturated seven-member heterocycle, with six carbon atoms and one sulfur atom." []
synonyms: ['organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]', 'Thiepines" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Thiepins" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D013846, MESH:D02.886.680, MESH:D03.383.886]']
xrefs: ['Wikipedia:Category\\:Thiepines']

name: Thiophenes
def: Compounds containing a five-membered aromatic moiety made up of one sulfur atom and four carbon atoms." []
xrefs: ['Wikipedia:Category\\:Thiophenes']

name: Triazines
def: Compounds containing a triazine ring, which is a heterocyclic ring, similar to the six-member benzene ring but with three carbons replaced by nitrogen atoms." []
xrefs: ['Wikipedia:Category\\:Triazines']

name: Triazoles
def: Compounds containing  a five-member aromatic ring of two carbon atoms and three nitrogen atoms." []

name: Phenanthridines and derivatives
def: Polycyclic compounds containing a phenanthridine moiety, which is a tricyclic system with two benzene rings joined by a pyridine forming a non-linear skeleton. Hydrogenated derivatives are also included." []

name: Eudesmane, isoeudesmane or cycloeudesmane sesquiterpenoids
def: Sesquiterpenoids with a structure based on the eudesmane skeleton." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['C15 isoprenoids (sesquiterpenes)" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR0103]', 'Cycloeudesmane sesquiterpenoids" NARROW LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010323]', 'eudesmane sesquiterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:62508]', 'Eudesmane sesquiterpenoids" NARROW LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010319]', 'Sesquiterpenes, Eudesmane" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.849.765.775]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:9780412466205 "John Buckingham (1993). Dictionary of Natural Products. Chapman and Hall/CRC; 1 edition (Dec 2 1993)']

name: Azetidines
def: Organic compounds containing a saturated four-member heterocycle where one nitrogen atom replaces a carbon atom." []

name: Aziridines
def: Organic compounds containing a saturated three-member heterocycle with one amino group and two methylene groups." []
xrefs: ['Wikipedia:Category\\:Aziridines']

name: Azirines
def: Organic compounds containing an unsaturated three-member heterocycle with one amino group and a double bond." []

name: Dioxolanes
def: Compounds containing a dioxolane ring, which is a five-membered saturated ring of two oxygen atoms and three carbon atoms. The dioxolanes are divided in 1,2-dioxolanes, and 1,3-dioxolanes." []
xrefs: ['Wikipedia:Category\\:Dioxolanes']

name: Oxathiolanes
def: Compounds containing an oxathiolane moiety, which consists of a saturated aliphatic five-member ring with one oxygen atom, a sulfur atom, and three carbon atoms. Isomers  of oxaphospholane include meta-oxathiolane, and ortho-oxathiolane." []

name: Oxazinanes
def: Compounds containing an oxazinane moiety, which consists of a saturated aliphatic six-member ring with one oxygen atom, a nitrogen atom, and four carbon atoms. Isomers  of oxaphospholane include 1,2-oxazinane, 1,3-oxazinane, and 1,4-oxazinane." []

name: Oxazolidines
def: Compounds containing an oxazolidine moiety, which consists of a saturated aliphatic five-member ring with one oxygen atom, one nitrogen, three carbon atoms, and two double bonds." []

name: Pteridines and derivatives
def: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a pteridine moiety, which consists of a pyrimidine fused to a pyrazine ring to form  pyrimido(4,5-b)pyrazine." []

name: Pterins and derivatives
def: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a pterin moiety, which consist of a pteridine ring bearing a ketone and an amine group to form 2-aminopteridin-4(3H)-one." []
synonyms: ['pterins" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26375]', 'Pterins" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D011622, MESH:D03.438.733.631, MESH:D23.767.831]']

name: Tetrazoles
def: Organic compounds containing a tetrazole ring, which is a five-member aromatic heterocycle made up of four nitrogen atoms and a one carbon atom." []
synonyms: ['tetrazoles" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35689]', 'Tetrazoles" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D013777, MESH:D03.383.129.617]', 'tetrazoles" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Hydrazines and derivatives
def: Compounds comprising the hydrazine functional group, with the general formula R1R2NNR3R4." [ISBN:0967855098]

name: Phenylhydrazines
def: Compounds containing a phenylhydrazide moiety, which consists of a hydrazide substituent attached to a phenyl group." []

name: Semicarbazides
def: Organic compounds containing the semicarbazide functional group with the general structure R1(N)R2NR3C(=O)N(R4)R5 (R1-R5=H, alkyl, aryl), a derivative of urea, where the amine group on one side has been replace by a hydrazine group." []

name: Semicarbazones
def: Organic compounds containing the semicarbazone functional group, with the general structure R2C=NNHC(=O)NH2." [ISBN:0967855098]
synonyms: ['hydrazone" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38532]', 'semicarbazones" EXACT IUPAC_TERM [ISBN:0967855098]', 'Semicarbazones" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D012664, MESH:D02.845.746]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Hydrazones
def: Compounds containing an N-Alkylidene derivative of hydrazine. They have the generic structure RNN=C(R')R\" (R,R',R\"= H or organyl group)." []

name: Imines
def: Compounds containing an imine functional group, with the general structure RN=CR2 (R = H, hydrocarbyl)." []

name: Ketones
def: Organic compounds  in which a carbonyl group is bonded to two carbon atoms R2C=O (neither R may be a hydrogen atom). Ketones that have one or more alpha-hydrogen atoms undergo keto-enol tautomerization, the tautomer being an enol." []
synonyms: ['ketone" EXACT ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:17087]', 'ketones" EXACT IUPAC_TERM [ISBN:0967855098]', 'Ketones" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D007659, MESH:D02.522]']

name: Acetophenones
def: Organic compounds containing the acetophenone structure." []

name: Benzophenones
def: Organic compounds containing a ketone attached to two phenyl groups." []
synonyms: ['benzophenones" EXACT ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22726]', 'Benzophenones" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D001577, MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.115.124, MESH:D02.522.223]']

name: Thioketones
def: Compounds in which the oxygen of a ketone has been replaced by divalent sulfur R2C=S ( R not H ). Thioketones that have an alpha-hydrogen interconvert with Thioenols. Moreover, they interconvert with thioaldehydes." []
synonyms: ['thioketone" EXACT ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36579]', 'thioketones" EXACT IUPAC_TERM [ISBN:0967855098]', 'Thiones" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Alpha-amino ketones
def: Ketones containing a carboxylic acid, and an amine group attached to the alpha carbon atom relative to C=O group." []
synonyms: ['ketone" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:17087]', 'organic amino compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50047]', 'Thiones" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D013871, MESH:D02.886.753]']

name: Benzopyrans
def: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a pyran ring. Pyran a six-membered heterocyclic, non-aromatic ring, made up of five carbon atoms and one oxygen atom and containing two double bonds." []
synonyms: ['benzopyran" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22727]', 'Benzopyranoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1311]', 'Benzopyrans" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D001578, MESH:D03.438.150, MESH:D03.830.219]']

synonyms: ['aldehyde" EXACT ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:17478]', 'aldehydes" EXACT IUPAC_TERM [ISBN:0967855098]', 'Aldehydes" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D000447, MESH:D02.047]', 'An aldehyde" EXACT UniProt_TERM []']

name: Quinomethanes
def: Organic compounds containing a cyclohexene or cyclohexadiene ring that bears a methylidene group and a ketone group. Isomers include m-quinomethane (6-methylidenecyclohex-2-en-1-one), o-quinomethane (5-methylidenecyclohex-2-en-1-one), and p-quinomethane (4-methylidenecyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-one)." []

def: Compounds bearing the group N3, viz. -N=N+=N-; usually attached to carbon, e.g. PhN3 phenyl azide or azidobenzene." [ISBN:0967855098]

def: Heteropolycyclic compounds with a structure containing isoindole, a benzo-fused pyrrole." []

name: Alkyl aryl ethers
def: Organic compounds containing the alkyl aryl ether functional group with the generic formula R-O-R' , where R is an alkyl group and R' is an aryl group." []

name: Alcohols and polyols
def: Organic compounds in which at least one hydroxyl functional group (-OH) is bound to a carbon atom, usually connected to other carbon or hydrogen atoms." []

name: Enediols
def: Compounds containing the enediol functional group, with the formula HO(R)C=C(R')OH." []

name: Enols
def: Compounds containing the enol functional group, with the structure HO(R)C=CR'. Ketones that have one or more alpha-hydrogen atoms undergo keto-enol tautomerization, the tautomer being an enol." []

name: 1,3-dicarbonyl compounds
def: Carbonyl compounds with the generic formula O=C(R)C(H)C(R')=O, where R and R' can be any group." [DOI:10.1016/j.tetasy.2010.04.045]
synonyms: ['a 1,3-dicarbonyl compound" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []', 'carbonyl compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36586]']

name: Phenols
def: Compounds containing a phenol moiety, which is a benzene bearing a hydroxyl group." []
synonyms: ['a phenol" EXACT UniProt_TERM []', 'Phenols" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D010636, MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.657]', 'phenols" EXACT ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33853]']

def: Compounds containing a 1,2-benzenediol moiety." []
synonyms: ['1,2-Benzenediols" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a 1,2-benzenediol" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a catechol" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []', 'catechols" EXACT ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33566]', 'Catechols" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D002396, MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.657.166]', 'o-Dihydroxybenzenes" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Ortho-Dihydroxybenzenes" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []']

synonyms: ['a quinol" RELATED UniProt_TERM []', 'hydroquinones" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24646]', 'Hydroquinones" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D006873, MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.657.393]']

def: Compounds containing a resorcinol moiety, which is a benzene ring bearing two hydroxyl groups at positions 1 and 3." []
synonyms: ['a resorcinol" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []', 'resorcinols" EXACT ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33572]', 'Resorcinols" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D012118, MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.657.852]']

name: Tyrosols and derivatives
def: Compounds containing a hydroxyethyl group attached to the C4 carbon of a phenol group." []

synonyms: ['Aminophenols" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.092.146.100, MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.657.050]', 'phenols" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33853]', 'substituted aniline" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:48975]']

name: Bisphenols
def: Methylenediphenols, HOC6H4CH2C6H4OH, commonly p,p-methylenediphenol, and their substitution products (generally derived from condensation of two equivalent amounts of a phenol with an aldehyde or ketone)." []

name: Macrolides and analogues

synonyms: ['macrolide" EXACT ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25106]', 'macrolides" EXACT IUPAC_TERM []', 'Macrolides and lactone polyketides" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK04]']

name: Aflatoxins
def: Difuranocoumarin derivatives in which the coumarin is fused to either a cyclopentenone (difurocoumarocyclopentenone series) or a lactone (difurocoumarolactone series)." []
synonyms: ['aflatoxin" EXACT ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22271]', 'Aflatoxins" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D000348, MESH:D03.438.150.119, MESH:D03.830.219.119, MESH:D23.946.587.142]', 'Aflatoxins and related substances" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK10]']

name: Tetracenequinones

name: Adamantanones
def: Organic compounds containing a ketone group is attached to the adamantane (tricyclo[3.3.1.1]decane) ring." []

name: Carbodiimides
def: Organic compounds containing a functional group consisting of the formula RN=C=NR." []
xrefs: ['Wikipedia:Category\\:Carbodiimides']

name: N-organohydroxylamines
def: Organic compounds comprising the hydroxylamine functional group, with the general structure R1ON(R2)R3 (R1,R3=H, organyl; R2 = organyl)." []

name: Epoxides
def: Compounds containing a cyclic ether with three ring atoms(one oxygen and two carbon atoms)." []
synonyms: ['An epoxide" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []', 'epoxide" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:32955]', 'Epoxy Compounds" EXACT MeSH_TERM [MESH:D004852, MESH:D02.355.291.411]', 'Oxiranes" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Lactams
def: Compounds containing a lactam ring, which is a cyclic amide of amino carboxylic acids, having a 1-azacycloalkan-2-one structure (or an analogue having unsaturation or heteroatoms replacing one or more carbon atoms of the ring)." []

name: Epothilones and analogues

xrefs: ['Wikipedia:Epothilone']

name: Beta lactams
def: Organic compounds containing a four-member lactam (a cyclic amide)." []

name: Caprolactams

name: Delta lactams

name: Gamma lactams
def: Organic compounds containing a gamma-lactam moiety, which consists of a five-member lactam ring." []

name: Thiolactams
def: Cyclic thioamides, obtained by replacing the oxygen atom from a lactam ring with sulfur." []

name: Penams

name: Phenylpropanoids and polyketides
def: Organic compounds that are synthesized either from the amino acid phenylalanine (phenylpropanoids) or the decarboxylative condensation of malonyl-CoA (polyketides). Phenylpropanoids are aromatic compounds based on the phenylpropane skeleton. Polyketides usually consist of alternating carbonyl and methylene groups (beta-polyketones), biogenetically derived from repeated condensation of acetyl coenzyme A (via malonyl coenzyme A), and usually the compounds derived from them by further condensations." name: Taxanes and derivatives
def: Diterpenoids with a structure based either on the taxane skeleton, or a derivative thereof. In term of phytochemistry, several derivatives of the taxane skeleton exist: 2(3->20)-abeotaxane, 3,11-cyclotaxane, 11(15->1),11(10->9)-abeotaxane, 3,8-seco-taxane, and 11(15->1)-abeotaxane, among others. def: Glycerophosphoserines  (molecules containing a serine moiety attached to the phosphate group linked to a glycerol) with one fatty acid bonded to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage." []

name: Chlorinated dibenzofurans
def: Organic compounds containing a chlorine atom attached to a dibenzofuran moiety." []

name: Benzo-p-dioxins
def: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a 1,4-dioxin ring." []

name: N-acyl-alpha-hexosamine-1-phosphates
def: N-acyl hexosamines in which the hexose is substituted by a phosphate group at position 1." []

name: Dibenzo-p-dioxins
def: Compounds containing a dibenzo-p-dioxin moiety, which consists of two benzene connected by a para-dioxin ring." []

def: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a 1,3-dioxin ring." []

name: Dioxins
def: Compounds containing a dioxin ring, which is a six-membered unsaturated ring of two oxygen atoms and four carbon atoms." []

name: Ortho dioxins
def: Compounds containing a dioxin ring, in which the two oxygen atoms are at positions 1 and 2 respectively." []

name: Para dioxins
def: Compounds containing a para dioxin moiety, which consists of an unsaturated six-member ring with two oxygen atoms at positions 1 and 4, as well as two CC double bonds." []

name: Neoflavones
def: Neoflavonoids with a structure based on the 4-phenylcoumarin skeleton." []

name: Colchicines
def: Compounds containing the benzo[a]heptalene based colchicin moiety or a derivative thereof. Colchicine is a tricyclic compound consisting of a benzene ring angularly fused to a tetrahydroheptalene  that carries a N-acetamide group." [PMCID:PMC3884533]

name: Lignans, neolignans and related compounds
def: Plant products of low molecular weight formed primarily from oxidative coupling of two p-propylphenol moieties. They can also be described as micromolecules with two phenylpropanoid units coupled together. They can be attached in various manners, like C5-C5', C8-C8'. Most known natural lignans are oxidized at C9 and C9¬¥ and, based upon the way in which oxygen is incorporated into the skeleton and on the cyclization patterns, a wide range of lignans of very different structural types can be formed." def: Glycerophosphoetahnolamines in which two fatty acids are bonded to the glycerol moiety through ester linkages." []

def: Glycerophosphoserines that contain exactly two fatty acyl chains attached to the glycerol moiety, one through an ester and the other through an ether linkage." []

name: Benzoxazines
def: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to an oxazine ring (a six-membered aliphatic ring with four carbon atoms, one oxygen atom, and one nitrogen atom)." []

name: 1-(1Z-alkenyl),2-acyl-glycerophosphates
def: Glycerophosphates that carry exactly one acyl chain attached to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage at the O2-position,  and one 1Z-alkenyl chain attached through an ether linkage at the O1-position." []

def: Inorganic non-metallic compounds containing a bisulfite as its largest oxoanion." []

def: Ceramides with phosphoinositol as substituent." []

name: Menthane monoterpenoids
def: Monoterpenoids with a structure based on the o-, m-, or p-menthane backbone. P-menthane consists of the cyclohexane ring with a methyl group and a (2-methyl)-propyl group at the 1 and 4 ring position, respectively. The o- and m- menthanes are much rarer, and presumably arise by alkyl migration of p-menthanes." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['Menthane monoterpenoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010209]', 'p-menthane monoterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25186]']

def: Glycerophosphates  in which the O-1 atom of the glycerol is bonded to a fatty acid (saturated or unsaturated) through an ether linkage, and the O-2 atom is bonded to another fatty acid through an ester linkage." []

name: Lysophosphatidylethanolamines
def: Glycerophosphoetahnolamines  (molecules containing an ethanolamine moiety attached to the phosphate group linked to a glycerol) with one  fatty acid chain bonded to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage." []

name: Xanthophylls
def: Carotenoids containing an oxygenated carotene backbone. Carotenes are characterized by the presence of two end-groups (mostly cyclohexene rings, but also cyclopentene rings or acyclic groups) linked by a long branched alkyl chain. Carotenes belonging form a subgroup of the carotenoids family. Xanthophylls arise by oxygenation of the carotene backbone." []
synonyms: ['a xanthophyll" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'C40 isoprenoids (tetraterpenes)" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR0107]', 'xanthophyll" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:27325]', 'Xanthophylls" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.326.271.665.202.868]']

name: Carotenes
def: A type of unsaturated hydrocarbons containing eight consecutive isoprene units. They are characterized by the presence of two end-groups (mostly cyclohexene rings, but also cyclopentene rings or acyclic groups) linked by a long branched alkyl chain. Carotenes belonging form a subgroup of the carotenoids family." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['a carotene" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'C40 isoprenoids (tetraterpenes)" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR0107]', 'carotenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23044]', 'Carotenoids" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.326.271.665.202]']

[]

name: GalNAcb1-3Gala1-4Galb1-4Glc- (Globo series)
def: Neutral glycosphingolipids in which the root sequence of the oligosaccharide moiety is GalNAcb1-3Gala1-4Galb1-4Glc." []

name: GalNAcb1-4GlcNAcb1-3Manb1-4Glc- (Arthro series)
def: Neutral glycosphingolipids in which the root sequence is GalNAcb1-4GlcNAcb1-3Manb1-4Glc." []

name: Galb1-3GlcNAcb1-3Galb1-4Glc- (Lacto series)
def: Neutral glycosphingolipids in which the root sequence of the oligosaccharide moiety is Galb1-3GlcNAcb1-3Galb1-4Glc." []

name: Galb1-4GlcNAcb1-3Galb1-4Glc- (Neolacto series)
def: Neutral glycosphingolipids in which the root sequence of the oligosaccharide moiety is Galb1-4GlcNAcb1-3Galb1-4Glc. The differ from lacto series because of their 1-4 (instead of 1-3) bond between Galb and GlcNacb." []

name: GalNAcb1-3Gala1-3Galb1-4Glc- (Isoglobo series)
def: Neutral glycosphingolipids in which the root sequence of the oligosaccharide moiety is GalNAcb1-3Gala1-3Galb1-4Glcb. The differ from lacto series because of their 1-3 (instead of 1-4) bond between Gala and Glacb." []

name: Betacyanins and derivatives
def: Organic compounds containing a glycoside of indolium-2-carboxylic acid attached, with the nitrogen ring of the indolium ring attached to an ethylpyridine-2,6-dicarboxylic acid derivative. Betacyanins are red nitrogenous pigments found in certain plants, such as beetroots." []

name: Betalains
def: Organic compounds belonging to the class of Betaxanthins or Betacyanins. This class also contains derivatives of betalamic acid, which is the precursor of betalains." []
synonyms: ['a betalain" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'betalain" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22861]', 'Betalains" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.092.877.233, MESH:D02.675.276.136, MESH:D03.132.124, MESH:D03.383.621.080, MESH:D12.125.072.050.875.064]']

name: GlcNAcb1-2Mana1-3Manb1-4Glc- (Mollu series)
def: Neutral glycosphingolipids in which the root sequence of the oligosaccharide moiety is GlcNAcb1-2Mana1-3Manb1-4Glc." []

name: Benzoxazinones
def: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to an oxazine ring (a six-member aliphatic ring with four carbon atoms, one oxygen atom, and one nitrogen atom) bearing a ketone group." []

name: Organothiophosphorus compounds
def: Organic derivatives of thiophosphonic acid, thiophosphoric acid, dithiophosphoric acid, or phosphorotrithioic acid, or derivatives thereof. Thiophosphonic acid, dithiophosphoric acid, thiophosphoric acid, and phosphorotrithioic acid are thiophosphorus compounds with the formula OP(O)(=S), OP(S)(=S)O, OP(O)(=S)O, and OP(=S)(S)S, respectively." []

name: Gangliosides
def: Lipid molecules composed of a glycosphingolipid (ceramide and saccharide) with one or more sialic acids linked on the sugar chain. They are usually oligoglycosylceramides derived from lactosylceramide and containing a sialic acid residue such as N-acetylneuraminic acid." []

name: Sulfatides
def: An hydrogen sulfate esters of glycosphingolipids." []
synonyms: ['a cerebroside 3-sulfate" RELATED UniProt_TERM []', 'a galactosylceramide sulfate" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a sulfoglycosphingolipid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'cerebroside 3-sulfates" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Galactosylceramide sulfates" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'sulfatides" RELATED IUPAC_TERM []', 'sulfoglycosphingolipid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36477]', 'Sulfoglycosphingolipids" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D10.390.470.025.837]', 'Sulfoglycosphingolipids (sulfatides)" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:SP0602]']

name: Alpha-amino acyl ester of carbohydrates
def: Compounds containing an amino acid esterified with a carbohydrate." [DOI:10.1016/j.ejmech.2006.04.005, DOI:10.1016/S0141-0229(99)00040-X, DOI:\:10.1016/j.enzmictec.2006.04.012]

name: Other mixed metal/non-metal oxoanionic compounds
def: Inorganic compounds containing a non-metal atom linked to a metallic oxoanionic moiety." []

name: Triazolopyrimidines
def: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing triazole ring fused to a pyrimidine ring. Triazole is a five-membered ring consisting of two carbon atoms and three nitrogen atoms. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions." []

name: Organic hypobromites
def: Organic compounds containing the hypobromite oxoanion, with the formula BrO-." []

name: Bile acids, alcohols and derivatives
def: Organic compounds containing an alcohol or acid derivative of cholic acid." []
synonyms: ['bile acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:3098]', 'Bile acids and derivatives" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST04]']

name: Thienoimidazolidines
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiophene ring fused to an imidazolidine ring. Thiophene is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one sulfur atom. Imidazolidine is 5-membered saturated ring of three carbon atoms, and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3-positions." []

name: Steroid glucuronide conjugates
def: Sterol lipids containing a glucuronide moiety linked to the steroid skeleton." []
synonyms: ['Glucuronides" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST0501]', 'steroid glucosiduronic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26763]']

name: Furoic acids
def: Organic compounds containing a furoic acid moiety, with a structure characterized by a furan ring bearing a carboxylic acid group at the C2 or C3 carbon atom." []

name: Intermetallic alkaline earth metal compounds
def: Inorganic compounds containing only metal atoms of at least two different types, where the heaviest atom is a lanthanide." []

name: Intermetallic lanthanide compounds
def: Inorganic compounds containing only metal atoms of at least two different types, where the heaviest atom is lanthanide." []

name: Intermetallic actinide compounds
def: Inorganic compounds containing only metal atoms of at least two different types, where the heaviest atom is a actinide metal." []

name: Intermetallic metalloid compounds
def: Compounds containing only metal atoms of at least two different types, where the heaviest atom is a metalloid." []
synonyms: ['Inorganic Chemicals" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D01]', 'inorganic molecular entity" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24835]', 'Metalloids" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D01.268.513]']

name: Intermetallic transition metal compounds
def: Inorganic compounds containing only metal atoms of at least two different types, where the heaviest atom is a transition metal." []

name: Intermetallic post-transition metal compounds
def: Inorganic compounds containing only metal atoms of at least two different types, where the heaviest atom is a post-transition metal." []

name: Tetrapyrroles and derivatives
def: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing four pyrrole rings joined by one-carbon units linking position 2 of one pyrrole ring to position 5 of the next." []

name: Miscellaneous inorganic compounds

name: Inorganic phosphorotrithioic acids and derivatives
def: Inorganic compounds containing a phosphorotrithioic acid group, with the structure OP(S)(S)=S (or SP(S)(S)=O)." []

name: Organophosphorotrithioic acids and derivatives
def: Organic compounds containing the organophosphorotrithioic acid structure or a derivative thereof. They have the general structure ROP(=S)(SR')SR\", where R-R\"= any atom." []

name: Organic thiophosphoric acid amides
def: Organic compounds containing the thiophosphoric acid amide functional group RN(R')OP(O)(O)=S, R,R'=H, alkyl, or aryl group." []

name: Thiophosphoric acid esters
def: Organic compounds containing the thiophosphoric acid functional group or a derivative thereof, with the general structure ROP(OR')(OR'')=S, where at least one R-group is an organyl group." []
synonyms: ['organic thiophosphate" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37512]', 'Thiophosphate esters" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Organic thiophosphoric acid halides
def: Organic compounds containing the thiophosphoric acid halide functional group, with the general structure RP(R')(X)=S, where R,R',R'' = O,N and X = halogen group." []
synonyms: ['acyl halide" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37579]', 'organothiophosphorus compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25716]']

name: Organic phosphoric acids
def: Organic compounds containing phosphoric acid, with the general structure OP(O)(=O)O." []

name: Retinoid esters
def: Ester derivatives of retinoic acid. These are obtained by formal condensation of the hydroxy group of retinol with the carboxy group of any carboxylic acid." []
synonyms: ['Retinoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR0109]', 'Retinoids" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.326.271.665.202.495]', 'retinyl ester" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:16179]']

name: Allylic alcohols
def: Organic compounds containing an alcohol group attached to the allyl functional group CH2=CHCH2." []

name: Organic hyponitrites
def: Organic compounds containing the hyponitrite oxoanion, with the formula ([ON=NO]2-." []

name: Benzofuranones
def: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a furanone." []

name: Quinodimethanes
def: Compounds containing a cyclohexene or cyclohexadiene ring that bears two methylidene groups." []

name: Triterpene glycosides
def: Triterpenoids in which an isoprene unit is glycosylated." []
synonyms: ['C30 isoprenoids (triterpenes)" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR0106]', 'triterpenoid saponin" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:61778]']

name: Piperidinones
def: Compounds containing a piperidine ring which bears a ketone." []

name: Piperidinediones
def: Compounds containing a piperidine ring which bears two ketones." []

name: Flavonoid O-glycosides
def: Compounds containing a carbohydrate moiety which is O-glycosidically linked to the 2-phenylchromen-4-one flavonoid backbone." []
synonyms: ['flavonoids" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:72544]', 'Flavonoids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK12]', 'glycoside" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24400]']

name: Catechins
def: Compounds containing a catechin moiety, which is a 3,4-dihydro-2-chromene-3,5.7-tiol." []
synonyms: ['catechin" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23053]', 'Flavans, Flavanols and Leucoanthocyanidins" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1202]']

name: Organosulfonamides
def: Compounds containing the sulfonamide functional group, an amide of sulfonic acid with the general structure R1S(=O)2N(R2)R3 (R1=alkyl, aryl; R2,R3=H, alkyl, aryl)." []
synonyms: ['organosulfur compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33261]', 'sulfonamide" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35358]', 'Sulfonamides" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.065.884]']

name: Biflavonoids and polyflavonoids
def: Organic compounds containing at least two flavan/flavone units. These units are usually linked through CC or C-O-C bonds. Some examples include C2-O-C3, C2-O-C4, C3'-C3''', and C6-C8''." [PMID:15978805, PMID:24716136]
synonyms: ['Biflavonoids and polyflavonoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1204]', 'flavonoid oligomer" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:72720]']

name: Catechin gallates
def: Organic compounds containing a gallate moiety glycosidically linked to a catechin." []
synonyms: ['catechin" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23053]', 'Flavans, Flavanols and Leucoanthocyanidins" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1202]']

name: N-epsilon-acyl lysines
def: Lysine derivatives containing an acyl group linked to the N-epsilon atom of lysine." []

name: Organic hypophosphites
def: Organic compounds containing the hypophosphite oxoanion, with the formula PO2‚àí." []

name: Organic iodates
def: Organic compounds containing the iodate oxoanion, with the formula IO3-." []
synonyms: ['iodate salt" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24856]', 'organic salt" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24868]']

name: Inorganic sulfuryl bromides
def: Inorganic compounds containing the sulfuryl bromide functional group, with the general structure BrS(R)(=O)=O (R=hetero atom)." []

name: Pterofurans
def: Compounds containing a 3-hydroxy-2,4-dimethoxyphenyl linked to the C2 atom of a benzofuran moiety." []

name: Bilirubins
def: Organic compounds containing a dicarboxylic acyclic tetrapyrrole derivative." []

name: Epigallocatechins
def: Compounds containing epigallocatechin or a derivative. Epigallocatechin is a flavan-3-ol containing a benzopyran-3,5,7-triol linked to a 3,4,5-hydroxyphenyl moiety." []
synonyms: ['catechin" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23053]', 'Flavans, Flavanols and Leucoanthocyanidins" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1202]']

name: Spatane and 4,10-secospatane diterpenoids
def: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the spatane or 4,10-secospatane skeleton. The spatane skeleton is formally derived from a prenylgermacrane by 1,5- and 6,10-cyclisation." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['Diterpenes" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.849.291]', 'diterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23849]', 'Spatane diterpenoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010437]']

name: Acyclic sesterterpenoids
def: Sesterterpenoids (compounds made of five consecutive isoprene units) that do not contain a cycle." []

name: 1-monoacylglycerols
def: Monoacylglycerols containing a glycerol acylated at the 1-position." []
synonyms: ['1-monoglyceride" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35759]', '1-monoglycerides" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a 1-monoacylglycerol" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a 1-monoglyceride" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Monoacylglycerols" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GL0101]']

name: Hydroxyanthraquinones
def: Compounds containing a hydroxyanthraquinone moiety, which consists of an anthracene bearing a quinone, and hydroxyl group." []

name: Disaccharide phosphates
def: Disaccharides carrying  one or more phosphate group on a sugar unit." []

name: Anthraquinone glycosides
def: Organic compounds containing an anthraquinone moiety glycosidically bound to a carbohydrate moiety." []

name: Cyclosporins
def: Cyclic depsipeptides containing the cyclosporin backbone." []

name: M-quinodimethanes
def: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring conjugated to two methylidene groups at carbon atoms 1 and 3, respectively." []

name: 2-monoacylglycerols
def: Monoacylglycerols containing a glycerol acylated at the 2-position." []
synonyms: ['2-acylglycerol" EXACT UniProt_TERM []', '2-monoglyceride" EXACT ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:17389]', '2-monoglycerides" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a 2-monoacylglycerol" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a 2-monoglyceride" EXACT CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Monoacylglycerols" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GL0101]']

name: Tetrahydrofuran lignans
def: Lignans with a structure that contains a tetrahydrofuran ring that arises from the joining of the two phenylpropanoid units." []

name: Carbonyl hydrates
def: Organic compounds containing two hydroxyl groups attached to a carbon atom." []

name: Retinoids
def: Oxygenated derivatives of 3,7-dimethyl-1-(2,6,6-trimethylcyclohex-1-enyl)nona-1,3,5,7-tetraene and derivatives thereof." [ISBN:0967855098]
synonyms: ['retinoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26537]', 'Retinoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR0109]', 'Retinoids" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.326.271.665.202.495]']

name: Rotenoids
def: Phenolic compounds containing a cis-fused tetrahydrochromeno[3,4-b]chromene nucleus. Many rotenoids contain an additional ring, e.g. rotenone. They are isoflavonoids characterized by the presence of an extra carbon atom in an additional heterocyclic ring." [ISBN:0967855098]
synonyms: ['a rotenoid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'rotenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:71543]', 'Rotenoid flavonoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1206]']

name: Pterocarpans
def: Benzo-pyrano-furano-benzene compounds, containing the  6H-[1]benzofuro[3,2-c]chromene skeleton. They are derivatives of isoflavonoids." []
synonyms: ['a pterocarpan" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'pterocarpans" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26377]', 'Pterocarpans" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1207]']

name: Carnitines
def: Organic compounds containing the quaternary ammonium compound carnitine." []
synonyms: ['amino-acid betaine" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22860]', 'Quaternary Ammonium Compounds" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D01.625.062.500]']

def: Lignans containing the arylnaphthalene skeleton, especially 9-(2H-1,3-benzodioxol-5-yl)-1H,3H-naphtho[2,3-c]furan-1-one or a derivative thereof. Arylnaphthalene lignans occur in nature and exhibit diverse biological activities." [DOI:10.1023/B\:PHYT.0000045487.02836.32, DOI:10.1023/B\:PHYT.0000045495.59732.58, ISBN:10.1039/NP9971400043]

name: Carbonic acid diesters
def: Compounds comprising the carbonic acid diester functional group." []

name: Isoflavans
def: Polycyclic compounds with a structure based on the 3-phenyl-3,4-dihydro-2H-1-benzopyran skeleton." []

name: Dibenzylbutyrolactone lignans
def: Lignan compounds containing a 3,4-dibenzyloxolan-2-one moiety." [DOI:10.1039/NP9971400043, DOI:10.5772/28471]
synonyms: ['a dibenzylbutyrolactone" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a dibenzylbutyrolactone lignan" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Dibenzylbutyrolactones" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'lignan" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25036]', 'Lignans" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.140.450]']

name: Neoflavonoids
def: Compounds with a structure based on the 4-phenylchromene backbone." []
synonyms: ['4-phenylbenzopyrans" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'neoflavonoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:71971]', 'Neoflavonoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1210]']

name: Flavones
def: Flavonoids with a structure based on the backbone of 2-phenylchromen-4-one (2-phenyl-1-benzopyran-4-one)." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['a flavone" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'flavones" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24043]', 'Flavones and Flavonols" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1211]']

name: Transition metal nitrites
def: Inorganic compounds in which the largest oxoanion is nitrite, and in which the heaviest atom not in an oxoanion is a transition metal." []
synonyms: ['nitrite salt" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:46648]', 'transition element molecular entity" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33497]']

name: Purine ribonucleoside monophosphates
def: Nucleotides consisting of a purine base linked to a ribose to which one monophosphate group is attached." []

name: Purine ribonucleoside diphosphates
def: Purine ribobucleotides with diphosphate group linked to the ribose moiety." []

name: Purine ribonucleoside triphosphates
def: Purine ribobucleotides with a triphosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety." []

name: Pyrimidine ribonucleoside monophosphates
def: Pyrimidine ribobucleotides with monophosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety." []

name: Pyrimidine ribonucleoside diphosphates
def: Pyrimidine ribonucleotides with diphosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety." []

name: Pyrimidine ribonucleoside triphosphates
def: Pyrimidine ribobucleotides with triphosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety." []

name: Dibenzocyclooctadiene lignans
def: Compounds containing a dibenzocyclooctadiene moiety, which consists of two hydroxylated benzene connected by a cycloheptene ring." [DOI:10.1023/B\:PHYT.0000045487.02836.32, DOI:10.1039/NP9971400043]
synonyms: ['2,2\'-Cyclolignans" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'lignan" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25036]', 'Lignans" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.140.450]']

name: Dibenzylbutanediol lignans
def: Lignan compounds containing a 2,3-dibenzylbutane-1,4-diol moiety." [DOI:10.1039/NP9971400043]

name: 1-aryltetralin lactones
def: Lignans with a structure containing the 1-aryltetralin skeleton, where the C9 and C9' atoms are joined to an oxygen atom to form a cyclopentanone." [DOI:10.1023/B\:PHYT.0000045487.02836.32]
synonyms: ['lactone" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25000]', 'lignan" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25036]', 'Lignans" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.140.450]']

name: Phenanthrolines
def: Aromatic polycyclic compounds containing the phenanthroline skeleton, which is a derivative of phenanthrene, and consists of two pyridine rings non-linearly joined by a benzene ring." []

name: Purine ribonucleoside polyphosphates
def: Purine ribobucleotides with polyphosphate (with 4 or more phosphate) group linked to the ribose moiety." []

name: Pyrimidine ribonucleoside polyphosphates
def: Pyrimidine ribobucleotides with polyphosphate (with 4 or more phosphate) group  linked to the ribose moiety." []

name: Benzopyrazoles
def: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a pyrazole ring. Pyrazole is a 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms and two adjacent nitrogen centers." []

name: Chalcones and dihydrochalcones
def: Organic compounds containing 1,3-Diphenylpropenone (benzylideneacetophenone), ArCH=CH(=O)Ar, or its derivatives formed by substitution." [PMID:15598564]
synonyms: ['Chalcones and dihydrochalcones" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1212]', 'flavonoids" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:72544]']

name: Aurone flavonoids
def: Flavonoids containing a 2-Benzylidene-1-benzofuran-3-one based core. Aurone flavonoids provide the bright yellow color of some important ornamental flowers, such as snapdragon (Antirrhinum majus)." [PMID:16233339]
synonyms: ['an aurone" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Aurone flavonoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1213]', 'aurones" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:72576]']

name: Flavanones
def: Compounds containing a flavan-3-one moiety, with a structure characterized by a 2-phenyl-3,4-dihydro-2H-1-benzopyran bearing a ketone at the carbon C3." []
synonyms: ['Flavan-3-ones" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'flavanones" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:28863]', 'Flavanones" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1214]']
xrefs: ['Wikipedia:Category\\:Flavanones']

name: Homoisoflavones
def: Homoisoflavonoids with a structure based on the chromone system. Chromone is a bicyclic compound consisting of a 1-benzopyran, which bears a ketone group at the 4-position." [PMID:20583326]

name: Naphthofurans
def: Compounds containing a furan ring fused to a naphthalene moiety. Furan is a 5 membered- ring aromatic ring with four carbon and one oxygen atoms. Naphthalene is a polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon  made up of two fused benzene rings." []

name: Pyridoxal 5'-phosphates
def: Pyridoxals (or derivative) containing a phosphate linked to the carbaldehyde group." []
synonyms: ['Pyridoxal 5\'-phosphate" RELATED UniProt_TERM []', 'vitamin B6 phosphate" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36970]']

name: Inorganic sulfuryl chlorides
def: Inorganic compounds containing the sulfuryl chloride functional group, with the general structure ClS(R)(=O)=O (R=hetero atom)." []

name: Serotonins
def: Compounds containing a serotonin moiety, which consists of an indole that bears an aminoethyl a position 2 and a hydroxyl group at position 5." []

name: 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholines
def: Glycerophosphocholines in which the glycerol is esterified with a fatty acid at O-1 position, and linked at position 3 to a phosphocholine." []
synonyms: ['1-acylglycerophosphocholine" RELATED UniProt_TERM []', '1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:58168]', 'Monoacylglycerophosphocholines" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GP0105]']

name: Tetrodotoxins
def: Compounds structurally characterized by the presence of the tetrodotoxin skeleton, which is based on 5,7-(epoxymethanooxy)quinazolin-10-olate moiety." []

name: Naphthopyrans
def: Compounds containing a pyran ring fused to a naphthalene moiety. Furan is a 6 membered-ring non-aromatic ring with five carbon and one oxygen atoms. Naphthalene is a polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon  made up of two fused benzene rings." []
synonyms: ['organic heterotricyclic compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26979]', 'organooxygen compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36963]']

name: Naphthopyranones
def: Compounds containing a naphthopyran skeleton where a ring carbon bears a carboxylic acid group. Naphthtopyran is made up of the pyran ring fused to a naphthalene ring system." []

name: Inorganic sulfuryl fluorides
def: Inorganic compounds containing the sulfuryl fluoride functional group, with the general structure FS(R)(=O)=O (R=hetero atom)." []

name: 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholines
def: Glycerophosphocholines in which the glycerol is esterified with a fatty acid at O-2 position, and linked at position 3 to a phosphocholine." []
synonyms: ['2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine(1+)" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:16728]', '2-acylglycerophosphocholine" RELATED UniProt_TERM []', '2-acylglycerophosphocholines" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', '2-lysophosphatidylcholine" RELATED UniProt_TERM []', 'Monoacylglycerophosphocholines" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GP0105]']

name: 1,2-diacylglycerols
def: Diacylglycerols containing a glycerol acylated at positions 1 and 2." []
synonyms: ['Diacylglycerols" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GL0201]', '1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol" RELATED UniProt_TERM []', '1,2-diglyceride" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:49172]', 'a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Diacylglycerol" BROAD UniProt_TERM []', 'Diglycerides" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D10.351.303]']

name: Depsides and depsidones
def: Polycyclic compounds that is either a polyphenolic compound composed of two or more monocyclic aromatic units linked by an ester bond (depside), or a compound containing the depsidone structure (depsidone)." []
synonyms: ['carbonyl compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36586]', 'Depsides and depsidones" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1308]']

name: Naphthopyranone glycosides
def: Compounds containing a carbohydrate moiety glycosidically linked to a naphthopyranone moiety." []

name: 1,3-diacylglycerols
def: Diacylglycerols containing a glycerol acylated at positions 1 and 3." []
synonyms: ['Diacylglycerols" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GL0201]', '1,3-diglyceride" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:47777]', 'a 1,3-diacyl-sn-glycerol" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Tyrosol esters
def: Tyrosol derivatives in the hydroxyl group of the hydroxyethyl moiety is replaced an o-ester group." []

name: Isochromanequinones
def: Polycyclic compounds containing an isochromanequinone, which is structurally characterized by a quinone fused to an isochromane, and forming a naphtho[2,3-c]pyran-6,9-dione skeleton." []

name: Tropones
def: Compounds containing a tropone ring, which is a cycloheptatrienone ring bearing a ketone group." []

name: Biopterins and derivatives
def: Coenzymes containing a 2-amino-pteridine-4-one derivative. They are mainly synthesized in several parts of the body, including the pineal gland." []

name: Carbonic acid ester halides
def: Compounds comprising the carbonic acid ester halide functional group." []
synonyms: ['carbonyl compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36586]', 'organohalogen compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36684]']

name: Long-chain fatty acyl CoAs
def: Acyl CoAs where the group acylated to the coenzyme A moiety is a long aliphatic chain of 13 to 21 carbon atoms." []
synonyms: ['Fatty acyl CoAs" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:FA0705]', 'LCFA-CoA" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'LCFA-CoAs" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'long-chain acyl-coenzyme A" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'long-chain acyl-coenzyme As" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'long-chain fatty acyl-CoA" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33184]', 'long-chain fatty acyl-coenzyme A" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'long-chain fatty acyl-coenzyme As" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Long-chain-acyl-CoA" RELATED UniProt_TERM []', 'Long-chain-acyl-CoAs" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Benzyl esters
def: Aromatic compounds containing an esterified benzyl group." []

name: Carbonic acid monoesters
def: Compounds comprising the carbonic acid monoester functional group." []

name: Acetals
def: Compounds having the structure R2C(OR')2 ( R' not Hydrogen) and thus diethers of geminal diols. Originally, the term was confined to derivatives of aldehydes (one R = H), but it now applies equally to derivatives of ketones (neither R = H ). Mixed acetals have different R' groups." []

name: Carboxylic acid imides
def: Carboxylic acid derivatives containing two carbonyl groups where the carbon atoms are both linked to the same nitrogen atom." []

name: N-substituted carboxylic acid imides
def: Compounds comprising an N-substituted carboxylic acid imide group, with the general structure R1N(C(R2)=O)C(R3)=O (R2,R3=H, alkyl, aryl; R1=Anything but H)." []

name: N-unsubstituted carboxylic acid imides
def: Compounds comprising an N-unsubstituted carboxylic acid imide group, with the general structure R1N(C(R2)=O)C(R3)=O (R1,R2,R3=H, alkyl, aryl)." []

name: Acyl cyanides
def: Organic compounds containing the cyanide functional group attached to an alkyl chain through an ester bond." []

name: Secondary alcohols
def: Compounds containing a secondary alcohol functional group, with the general structure HOC(R)(R') (R,R'=alkyl, aryl)." []
synonyms: ['secondary alcohol" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35681]', 'secondary alcohol" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Primary carboxylic acid amides
def: Compounds comprising primary carboxylic acid amide functional group, with the general structure RC(=O)NH2." []

name: Secondary carboxylic acid amides
def: Compounds containing a secondary carboxylic acid amide functional group, with the general structure RC(=O)N(R')H (R,R'=alkyl, aryl)." []

name: Tertiary carboxylic acid amides
def: Compounds containing an amide derivative of carboxylic acid, with the general structure RN(R1)C(R2)=O (R1-R2 any atom but H)." []

name: Enolates
def: Deprotonated anions of enols. They have diverse forms with either of the general structure [R1]C([R2])=C([R3])[O-], RC([CH2-])=O, or R1C(R1)=COM (M=metal)." []
synonyms: ['an enolate" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organooxygen compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36963]']

name: Thiohemiaminal derivatives
def: Compounds containing the thiohemiaminal group with the general structure R1SC(R2)(R3)N(R4)R5 (R1-R5=H, alkyl, aryl)." []

name: Carboxylic acid amide acetals
def: Carboxylic acid derivatives two hydroxyl groups attached to a carbon atom, which in turn is linked to a nitrogen atom(substituted or not)." []
synonyms: ['organic amino compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50047]', 'organic hydroxy compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33822]']

name: Organic diazonium salts
def: Organic compounds comprising the diazonium functional group, with the general structure R-N=N+." []
synonyms: ['diazo compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:39444]', 'Diazonium Compounds" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.172.383]']

name: Long-chain ceramides
def: Ceramides bearing a long chain fatty acid." []
synonyms: ['ceramide" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:17761]', 'Ceramides" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:SP02]', 'Ceramides" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.065.313]']

name: Tertiary alcohols
def: Compounds in which a hydroxy group, -OH, is attached to a saturated carbon atom R3COH (R not H )." []
synonyms: ['tertiary alcohol" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26878]', 'tertiary alcohols" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Physalins and derivatives
def: Steroidal constituents of Physalis plants which possess an unusual 13,14-seco-16,24-cyclo-steroidal ring skeleton (where the bond that is normally present between the 13 and 14 positions in other steroids is broken while a new bond between positions 16 and 24 is formed)." []

name: Organic thiocarbonic acid derivatives
def: Organic compounds containing the thiocarbonic acid structure or a derivative thereof." []

name: Ketimines
def: Organic compounds bearing the ketimine functional group, with the general structure R2C=NR' ( R is not a hydrogen )." []

name: Tropolones
def: Compounds containing tropone ring with a hydroxyl group at ring position 2." []

name: Aminocyclitol glycosides
def: Organic compounds containing an amicocyclitol moiety glycosidically linked to a carbohydrate moiety. There are two major classes of aminoglycosides containing a 2-streptamine core. They are called 4,5- and 4,6-disubstituted 2-deoxystreptamines." [PMCID:PMC89199]

name: Phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphates
def: Phosphatidylinositol bisphosphates in which the two phosphate groups are at C-4 and C-5 of the inositol moiety." []
synonyms: ['a phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Diacylglycerophosphoinositol bisphosphates" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GP0801]', 'phosphatidylinositol bisphosphate" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37328]']

name: 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamines
def: Glycerophoethanolamines in which the glycerol is esterified with a fatty acid at O-1 position, and linked at position 3 to a phosphoethanolamine." []

name: Acyclic allenes
def: Acyclic hydrocarbons (and by extension, derivatives formed by substitution) having two double bonds from one carbon atom to two others." []

name: Cyclic allenes
def: Cyclic hydrocarbons (and by extension, derivatives formed by substitution) having two double bonds from one carbon atom to two others." []

name: 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamines
def: Glycerophoethanolamines in which the glycerol is esterified with a fatty acid at O-2 position, and linked at position 3 to a phosphoethanolamine." []

name: 1-acyl-glycerol-3-phosphoserines
def: Monoacylglycerol-3-phosphoserines with a fatty acyl chain linked to the O1-atom of the glycerol moiety." []
synonyms: ['1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphatidylserine" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', '1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphatidylserines" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', '1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:52603]', 'Monoacylglycerophosphoserines" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GP0305]']

name: 2-acyl-glycerol-3-phosphoserines
def: Monoacylglycerol-3-phosphoserines with a fatty acyl chain linked to the O2-atom of the glycerol moiety." []

name: Monoacylglycerophosphates
def: Monacylglyerophosphates in which the glycerol moiety is esterified at only position, and is attached to a phosphate group." []
synonyms: ['monoacylglycerol phosphate" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:16961]', 'monoacylglycerol phosphate" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Monoacylglycerophosphates" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GP1005]']

name: 1-acylglycerol-2-phosphates
def: Monacylglyerophosphates in which the glycerol moiety is esterified at position 1 and attached to a phosphate group through the O-2 atom." []

name: 1-acylglycerol-3-phosphates
def: Lysophosphatidic acids where the glycerol is esterified with a fatty acid at O-1 position." []
synonyms: ['1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate" RELATED UniProt_TERM [CHEBI:16975]', '1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphates" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', '1-acylglycerol-3-phosphate" RELATED UniProt_TERM []', '2-lysophosphatidic acid" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:76629]', '2-lysophosphatidic acids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a 1-acylglycerol-3-phosphate" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a 2-lysophosphatidic acid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate" BROAD UniProt_TERM []', 'Monoacylglycerophosphates" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GP1005]']

name: Cucurbitacins
def: Polycyclic compounds containing the tetracyclic cucurbitane nucleus skeleton, 19-(10->9b)-abeo-10alanost-5-ene (also known as 9b-methyl-19-nor lanosta-5-ene), with a variety of oxygenation functionalities at different positions." [ASIN:B004GEAWLS]
synonyms: ['Cholesterol and derivatives" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST0101]', 'cucurbitacin" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:16219]', 'Cucurbitacins" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.849.919.138]']

name: Cucurbitacin glycosides
def: Polycyclic compounds containing a carbohydrate derivative glycosidically linked to a curcubitane nucleus." [DOI:10.1016/0031-9422(89)80230-4]
synonyms: ['Cholesterol and derivatives" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST0101]', 'cucurbitacin" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:16219]', 'Cucurbitacins" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.849.919.138]', 'glycoside" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24400]']

def: Lysophosphatidic acids where the glycerol is esterified with a fatty acid at O-2 position." []
synonyms: ['2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:17936]', 'acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate" BROAD UniProt_TERM []', 'Monoacylglycerophosphates" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GP1005]']

name: Long-chain 1-acylglycerol-3-phosphates
def: 1-Acylglycerophosphates in which a long-chain fatty acid is esterified to the glycerol moiety." []

name: Polysaccharide phosphates
def: Carbohydrates containing more than 10 sugar units, one of which bear one or more phosphate groups." []

name: Steroid esters
def: Compounds containing a steroid moiety which bears a carboxylic acid ester group." []
synonyms: ['a sterol ester" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'A steryl ester" RELATED UniProt_TERM []', 'steroid ester" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:47880]', 'Steryl esters" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST0102]']

name: Sulfated steroids
def: Sterol lipids containing a sulfate group attached to the steroid skeleton." []

name: Aminotriazines
def: Organic compounds containing an amino group attached to a triazine ring." []

name: Aminopyrazines
def: Organic compounds containing an amino group attached to a pyrazine ring." []

name: Oxetane amino acids and derivatives
def: Sugar amino acids containing an oxetane ring between the carboxy- and the amino terminals of the amino acid chain." [DOI:\:10.1016/j.tetasy.2007.08.004]
xrefs: ['DOI:\\:10.1016/j.tetasy.2007.08.004 "Risseeuw MDP et al (2007). Tetrahedron: Asymmetry 18; 2001‚Äì2010']

def: Sugar amino acids containing a furan ring." [DOI:\:10.1016/j.tetasy.2007.08.004]

Furanoid sugar amino acids as dipeptide mimics in design of analogs of vasoactive intestinal peptide receptor binding inhibitor. J Pept Res. 2005 Aug;66(2):75-84.']

name: Pyranoid amino acids and derivatives
def: Compounds containing a (hydro)pyran ring bearing unprotected amino and carboxylic acid functionalities." [DOI:\:10.1016/j.tetasy.2007.08.004]
xrefs: ['DOI:\\:10.1016/j.tetasy.2007.08.004 "Risseeuw MDP et al (2007). Tetrahedron: Asymmetry 18; 2001‚Äì2010']

def: Sugar amino acids in which the amino acid is attached to or partly borne within a bicyclic ring system." [DOI:10.1007/s00726-007-0588-y]
synonyms: ['organonitrogen compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35352]', 'organooxygen compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36963]']

name: Glycopeptides and derivatives
def: Compounds in which a carbohydrate component is linked to a peptide through any covalent bond." []

name: Spirostanes and derivatives
def: Steroidal alkaloids with a structure containing a spirostane skeleton. Spirostanes are 16b,22:22,26-diepoxycholestanes, or 22,26-epoxyfurostans. The sixth ring so formed is known as ring F. Chemically, the spiro centre at C-22 has the character of an internal acetal derived from a 16b, 26-dihydroxycholestan-22-one." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['oxaspiro compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37948]', 'Spirostanols and derivatives" NARROW LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST0108]', 'steroid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35341]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:9780412466205 "John Buckingham (1993). Dictionary of Natural Products. Chapman and Hall/CRC; 1 edition (Dec 2 1993)']

name: Furostanes and derivatives
def: Compounds containing or derived from the steroid parent furostane, which is a 16b,22-epoxycholestane derivative, the extra ring being labeled as\nring E." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['Furostanols and derivatives" NARROW LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST0107]', 'oxaspiro compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37948]', 'steroid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35341]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:9780412466205 "John Buckingham (1993). Dictionary of Natural Products. Chapman and Hall/CRC; 1 edition (Dec 2 1993)']

name: Furospirostanes and derivatives
def: Heterocyclic steroids containing a furospirostane moiety, which a skeleton characterized by the presence of a 1,6-dioxaspiro[4.4]nonane ring system and an androstane moiety." []
synonyms: ['Furospirostanols and derivatives" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST0109]', 'oxaspiro compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37948]', 'steroid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35341]']

name: Solanidines and derivatives
def: Steroids with a structure based on the solanidane skeleton.  Solanidane arises from the conversion of a cholestane side-chain into a bicyclic system." []
synonyms: ['alkaloid" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22315]', 'organic heteropolycyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38166]', 'Solanidines and alkaloid derivatives" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST0115]', 'steroid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35341]']

name: Spirosolanes and derivatives
def: Steroidal alkaloids with a structure containing a spirosolane skeleton. Siporosolane is a polycyclic compound that is characterized by a 1-oxa-6-azaspiro[4.5]decane moiety where the oxolane ring is fused to a docosahydronaphth[2,1:4',5']indene ring system. Spirosolane arises from the conversion of a cholestane side-chain into a bicyclic system containing a piperidine and a tetrahydrofuran ring." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['azaspiro compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35624]', 'oxaspiro compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37948]', 'steroid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35341]', 'Sterol Lipids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:9780412466205 "John Buckingham (1993). Dictionary of Natural Products. Chapman and Hall/CRC; 1 edition (Dec 2 1993)']

name: Gingerols
def: Compounds containing a gingerol moiety, which is structurally characterized by a 4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl group substituted at the C6 carbon atom by a 5-hydroxy-alkane-3-one." []
synonyms: ['beta-hydroxy ketone" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:55380]', 'monomethoxybenzene" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25235]', 'phenols" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33853]']

name: Gingerdiols
def: Compounds containing a gingerdiol moiety, which is structurally characterized by a 4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl group substituted at the C6 carbon atom by an alkane-2,4-diol." []
synonyms: ['glycol" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:13643]', 'monomethoxybenzene" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25235]', 'phenols" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33853]']

name: Gingerdiones
def: Compounds containing a gingerdione moiety, which is structurally characterized by a 4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl group substituted at the C6 carbon atom by an alkane-2,4-dione." []
synonyms: ['beta-diketone" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:67265]', 'monomethoxybenzene" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25235]', 'phenols" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33853]']

name: Shogaols
def: Ginger derivatives containing a shogaol moiety, which consists of a benzene ring bearing a dec-4-en-3-one moiety, a methoxyphenyl group, a hydroxyl group and at positions 1, 3, and 4, respectively." []
synonyms: ['enone" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:51689]', 'monomethoxybenzene" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25235]', 'phenols" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33853]']

name: Paradols
def: Compounds containing a paradol moiety, which is consists of a benzene ring with a decan-3-one moiety, a methoxyl group, and a hydroxyl group at positions 1,3, and 4 respectively." []
synonyms: ['ketone" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:17087]', 'monomethoxybenzene" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25235]', 'phenols" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33853]']

name: Hydrolyzable tannins
def: Tannins with a structure characterized by either of the following models. In model 1, the structure contains galloyl units (in some cases, shikimic acid units) that are linked to diverse polyol carbohydrate-, catechin-, or triterpenoid units. In model 2, contains at least two galloyl units C-C coupled to each other, and do not contain a glycosidically linked catechin unit." [DOI:10.1002/jsfa.2577]
xrefs: ['DOI:10.1002/jsfa.2577 "Mueller-Harvey I (2006). Unraveling the conundrum of tannins in animal nutrition and health. 86:13, pp 2010-2037']

name: Phlorotannins
def: Tannins which is formed by oligomerization of phloroglucinol. Phloroglucinol is an aromatic compound, which consists of a benzene ring bearing one hydroxyl group at the 1-,3-, and 5-positions." [PMID:9131591]

name: Complex tannins
def: Tannins made of a catechin bound to a gallotannin or elagitannin." []

name: Beta hydroxy acids and derivatives
def: Compounds containing a carboxylic acid substituted with a hydroxyl group on the C3 carbon atom." []

name: Hydroxyquinolones
def: Compounds containing a quinoline moiety bearing a hydroxyl group and a ketone. Quinoline or benzo[b]pyridine is a bicyclic compound that consists of benzene fused to a pyridine." []

name: Hydroquinolines
def: Derivatives of  quinoline in which in which at least one double bond in the quinoline moiety are reduced by adding two hydrogen atoms." []

name: Hydroquinolones
def: Compounds containing a hydrogenated quinoline bearing a ketone group." []

name: Oxaborine derivatives
def: Compounds containing a six-member aliphatic heterocycle made up of one oxygen atom, a boron atom, and three carbon atoms." []

name: Other glycerophosphoinositol phosphates
def: Glycerophosphoinositol phosphates not belonging to Lysophosphatidylinositol Phosphates, or the Phosphatidylinositol Phosphates." []
synonyms: ['glycerophosphoinositol phosphate" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35771]', 'Glycerophospholipids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GP]', 'Glycerophospholipids" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D10.570.755.375.760.400]']

name: Diacylglycerophosphodiradylglycerols
def: Glycerophosphodiradylglycerols that carry exactly two acyl chains attached to the glycerol moiety through ester linkages." []

name: Lysophosphatidylglycerophosphates
def: Glycerophosphates (molecules containing a phosphate group linked to a glycerol) where the glycerol is esterified with one fatty acid." []

name: Phosphoglycosphingolipids
def: Sphingolipids containing a carbohydrate linked to the sphingoid base (sphingosine, sphinganine) through a phosphate group." []

name: Fatty alcohol esters
def: Ester derivatives of a fatty alcohol." []
synonyms: ['carboxylic ester" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33308]', 'Fatty Acyls" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:FA]']

name: Wax esters
def: Mixtures of long-chain apolar lipids. They are usually esters of an alcohol other than glycerol and a long chain acid." []
synonyms: ['Fatty esters" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:FA07]', 'wax ester" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:10036]']

name: Pyrethrins
def: Pyrethroids with a structure based on a skeleton that is characterized by the presence of a chrysanthemic acid esterified with a cyclopentenone derivative." []

name: Chloropropanol esters
def: Compounds containing an ester derivative of chloropropanol." [PMID:22017647]
synonyms: ['carboxylic ester" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33308]', 'Fatty esters" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:FA07]', 'organochlorine compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36683]']

def: Glycosylglycerophospholipids, where the glycerol moiety is esterified with two fatty acyl chains." []
synonyms: ['a 1,2-diacylglycosylglycerophospholipid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a diacylglycosylglycerophospholipid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Diacylglycosylglycerophospholipids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GP1401]', 'glycophospholipid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24397]']

name: Quinacridines
def: Compounds containing a quinacridine moiety, which consists of a quinoline fused to an acridine." []

name: Oxepanes
def: Compounds containing an oxepane ring, which is a seven-member saturated aliphatic heterocycle with one oxygen and six carbon atoms." []

name: Piperidinylpyridines
def: Compounds containing a piperidinylpyridine moiety, which consists of a piperidine linked to a pyridine by a single bond that is not pat of a ring." []

name: Dioxopiperazines
def: Compounds containing a piperazine ring bearing two ketone groups. These include the alkaloid class of naturally occurring 2,5-dioxopiperazines." []
synonyms: ['a thiodioxopiperazine" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Diketopiperazines" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'piperazinone" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:46846]']
xrefs: ['PMID:24615992 "Amatov T and Jahn U (2014). Gliotoxin: Nature s Way of Making the Epidithio Bridge. Angew.Chem.Int.Ed. 2014 , 53 , 3312 ‚Äì 3314.']

name: Thiodioxopiperazines
def: Compounds containing a piperazine ring which bears two ketone groups and a sulfanyl group." []
synonyms: ['a thiodioxopiperazine" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'thiocarbonyl compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50492]']

name: Pyrroloindoles
def: Compounds containing a pyrroloindole moiety, which is a tricyclic heterocycle which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to an indole. Pyrrole is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom. Indole is a bicyclic  compound consisting of a six-membered benzene ring fused to a five-membered nitrogen-containing pyrrole ring." []

name: Pyrroloquinolines
def: Compounds containing a pyrroloquinoline moiety, which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to a quinoline." []

name: Furanochromones
def: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a furan ring fused to a 1-benzopyran-4-one ring system." []
synonyms: ['organic heterotricyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26979]', 'oxacycle" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38104]']

name: Benzochromones
def: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to the benzene moiety of chromone (1,4-benzopyrone)." []

name: Flavonoid C-glycosides
def: Compounds containing a carbohydrate moiety which is C-glycosidically linked to the 2-phenylchromen-4-one flavonoid backbone." []
synonyms: ['C-glycosyl compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:20857]', 'Flavonoids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK12]', 'flavonoids" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:72544]']

name: Aurone O-glycosides
def: Aurone flavonoids containing a carbohydrate moiety O-glycosidically bound to the aurone skeleton." []
synonyms: ['Aurone flavonoids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1213]', 'aurones" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:72576]', 'glycoside" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24400]']

name: Chalcone- and dihydrochalcone O-glycosides
def: Compounds containing a O-glycosylated chalcone or dihydrochalcone moiety." []
synonyms: ['Chalcones and dihydrochalcones" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1212]', 'flavonoids" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:72544]', 'glycoside" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24400]']

name: Organic antimonates
def: Organic compounds containing the antimonate oxoanion, with the formula Sb(OH)6-." []

name: Rotenoid O-glycosides
def: Compounds containing a carbohydrate moiety glycosidically linked to the rotenoid backbone at the C8-position." []
synonyms: ['glycoside" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24400]', 'rotenoid" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:71543]', 'Rotenoid flavonoids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1206]']

name: Coumaronochromones

def: Glycolipids structurally characterized by a glycosyl head group, in this case a rhamnose moiety, and a 3-(hydroxyalkanoyloxy)alkanoic acid (HAA) fatty acid tail." [DOI:10.1007/s00253-010-2498-2]

name: Fatty acyl glycosides
def: Compounds containing fatty acyl chain linked to a carbohydrate moiety through a glycosidic bond. Fatty acyl glycosides are composed of a glycosyl moiety (one or several units) linked to one hydroxyl group of a fatty alcohol or of a phosphorylated alcohol (phosphoprenols), a hydroxy fatty acid or to one carboxyl group of a fatty acid (ester linkage) or to an amino alcohol." [Cyberlipid:glycolip/glyl0006.htm]

name: Ginkgolides and bilobalides
def: Diterpene lactones with a structure based either on the gingkolide or the bilobalide skeleton. The ginkgolide skeleton is a very rigid structure consisting of hexacyclic C20 trilactone. The cis-fused F/A/D/C ring junction forms an empty semi-ball hole, the D ring contains a cage form tetrahydrofuran ring which occupies the center of the empty hole, and the oxygen atoms of the D,C and F ring and 10-hydroxyl group consist of an analogous crown ether structure." [ISBN-13:978-1-4398-6077-9]

name: Amaryllidaceae alkaloids
def: Isoquinoline alkaloids with a skeleton deriving from lycorine, norbelladine, homolycorine, hemanthamine, crinine, tazettine, montanine, plicamine, galanthindole, galanthamine, gracilline, among others. Amaryllidaceae Alkaloids represent a large group of biogenetically related isoquinoline alkaloids that are found exclusively in plants belonging to this family of Amaryllidaceae. This group of alkaloids is also derived from two tyrosine units which combine, with loss of one carbon atom, to give a benzylphenylethylamine precursor unit, e.g. Norbelladine, which by various oxidative cyclisation processes, prominent among which are phenol oxidative coupling reactions, can give rise to the nine major skeletal groups." [ISBN:978-81-7895-528-5, ISBN:9780412466205]

name: Aromadendrane sesquiterpenoids
def: Sesquiterpenoids with a structure based on an aromadendrane (a cyclopropa[e]azulene derivative) skeleton. Some aromadendrane sesquiterpenoids are found in essential oils. Certain aromadendrane Sesquiterpenoids from the Leaves of Xylopia brasiliensis were found to possess antifungal activities." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['Aromadendrane sesquiterpenoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010343]', 'Sesquiterpenes" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.849.765]', 'sesquiterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26658]']

name: Curan alkaloids
def: Compounds containing the pentacyclic curan skeleton, which is structurally characterized by the presence of a pentacyclic 3,5-ethanopyrrolo[2,3-d]carbazole framework." []

name: Thiaergolines
def: Ergoline analogues, obtained by replacing the oxygen atom in the indole moiety (of the ergoline backbone) by a sulfur atom." []

name: Oxamorphinans
def: Polycyclic compounds with a four-ring skeleton with three condensed six-member rings forming a partially hydrogenated naphthopyran moiety, one of which is aromatic while the two others are alicyclic." []

name: Yohimbine alkaloids
def: Alkaloids containing the pentacyclic yohimban skeleton. The Yohimbinoid alkaloids contain a carbocyclic ring E arising through C-17 to C-18 bond formation in a corynantheine precursor." [ISBN:978-1-4200-7769-8]
synonyms: ['yohimban alkaloid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:27358]', 'Yohimbinoid alkaloids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Ochratoxins and related substances
def: A group of chemically related metabolites containing a 3,4-dihydro-3-methylisocoumarin moiety linked through a carboxyl group to L-beta-phenylalanine by a secondary amine bond." [DOI:10.1021/ba-1976-0149.ch005]
synonyms: ['isochromanes" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38762]', 'monocarboxylic acid amide" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:29347]', 'phenylalanine derivative" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25985]']

name: Trichothecenes
def: Sesquiterpene mycotoxins structurally characterized by the presence of an epoxide ring and a benzopyran derivative with a variant number of hydroxyl, acetyl, or other substituents. The most important structural features causing the biological activities of trichothecenes are the 12,13-epoxy ring, the presence of hydroxyl or acetyl groups at appropriate positions on the trichothecene nucleus and the structure and position of the side-chain." [HTTP:leitl.org/docs/biowar/Ch-34.pdf, ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['Sesquiterpenes" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.849.765]', 'Trichothecane sesquiterpenoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010318]', 'trichothecene" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:55517]']

synonyms: ['a gliotoxin" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organic disulfide" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35489]', 'organic heterotetracyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38163]', 'pyrazinoindole" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:64130]']

name: Fumonisins
def: Diesters of propane-1,2,3-tricarboxylic acid (TCA) and similar long-chain aminopolyol backbones (for FB1: 2S-amino-12S,16R-dimethyl-3S,5R,10R,14S,15R-pentahydroxyeicosane). Structurally, fumonisins resemble the sphingoid bases sphinganine (SA) and sphingosine (SO) to which TCA groups have been added at the C-14 and C-15 positions." [DOI:10.3390/ijms9112062]

name: Ellipticine alkaloids
def: Compounds containing a pyrido[4,3-b]carbazole moiety." [DOI:10.3998/ark.5550190.0009.315]
synonyms: ['an ellipticine alkaloid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'indole alkaloid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38958]', 'pyrido[4,3-b]carbazoles" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Pyridocarbazole alkaloids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Ajmaline-sarpagine alkaloids
def: Organic compounds containing either of the ajmalan, sarpagan skeleton, or derivative thereof. The Sarpagine (Akuammidine) group, based on the sarpagan nucleus, arises from bond formation between C-16 and C-5 of the corynantheine precursor.  Ajmaline alkaloids are based on a 17,19-secoyohimban skeleton (oxayohimban) which is invariably present as an ether." [ISBN:978-1-4200-7769-8, ISBN:9780412466205]

Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions." []

They are produced by Aspergilus spp. and Bipolaris spp." [ISBN-13:978-0849349041]

name: Peptoids

Alpha-peptoids (commonly referred to as peptoids) are N-substituted glycines. But in general, this class also extends to oligo- or polymers of beta-, gamma-, delta peptoid analogues of amino acids." [PMCID:PMC50132]

name: Quassinoids
def: A group of compounds chemically degraded from triterpenes. According to their basic skeleton, quassinoids are categorized into five distinct groups, C-18, C-19, C-20, C-22 and C-25 types. The C-20 quassinoids can be further classified into two types, tetracyclic and the pentacyclic. The tetracyclic variety does not have oxygenation at C-20, while the pentacyclic quassinoids possess additional oxygenation at C-20 that allows for the formation of an additional ring." [PMID:15638734]
