synonyms: ['benzoquinones" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22729]', 'Benzoquinones" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.806.250]', 'Quinones" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.806]']

name: O-quinones
def: Quinones where the two C=O groups are attached at the 1- and 2-positions, respectively." []

name: M-quinones
def: Quinones where the two C=O groups are attached at the 1- and 3-positions, respectively." []

name: P-quinones
def: Quinones where the two C=O groups are attached at the 1- and 4-positions, respectively." []

name: O-iminoquinones
def: O-quinones that carry an imine group." []

name: Diazinanes
def: Organic compounds containing diazinane, a six-membered saturated heterocycle containing four carbon atoms and two nitrogen atoms." []
synonyms: ['organic heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24532]', 'organonitrogen heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38101]']

name: P-iminoquinones
def: P-quinones that carry an imine group." []

name: Glycerol ethers
def: Lipids containing an ether derivative of glycerol." []

name: Azines
def: Hydrazine derivatives in which the hydrazine group is conjugated to two aldehydes (forming aldazines) or ketones (forming ketazines)." []

name: Azomethines
def: Compounds having the general structure RN=CR2 (where R is not a hydrogen atom)." [ISBN:0967855098]
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Shiff bases
def: Aldimines where the nitrogen atom of the aldimine group is linked to an alkyl or aryl group." []

name: Primary aldimines
def: Aldimines where the nitrogen atom of the aldimine group is linked to a hydrogen atom." []

name: Azomethine imides
def: 1,3-dipolar N-imides of azomethines. They have the general formula R1C(R2)=[N+](R3)[N-]R4 or  R1[C-](R2)[N+](R3)=[N-]R4, where R1-R4 = organyl group." [ISBN:0967855098]

xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Nitrones
def: N-oxides of imines, with the general structure R1C(R2)=[N+](R3)[O-] (R3 is not an Hydrogen atom)." [ISBN:0967855098]
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Azomethine ylides
def: 1,3-Dipolar  Compounds having the general structure [C-][N+]=C(R)(R')." [ISBN:0967855098]
synonyms: ['an azomethine ylide" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'azomethine ylide" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:51159]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Azonic acids and derivatives
def: Organic acids with the general formula R[N+](OR')(OR'')O- (R = organyl; R',R\" = any atom)." []

name: Adianane, fernane, filicane, and neohopane triterpenoids
def: Triterpenoids with a structure based either on the adianane, fernane, filicane, or neohopane skeleton. These are obtained by rearrangement of the moretane skeleton." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['Neohopane, fernane, adianane and filicane triterpenoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010620]', 'triterpenoid" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36615]']

name: Thiophthalic anhydrides
def: Organic heterocyclic aromatic compounds that contain a 1,3-dihydro-2-benzothiophene-1,3-dione moiety." [DOI:10.1021/ol200336c]
synonyms: ['2-benzothiophenes" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38837]', 'a thiophthalic anhydride" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: N-acyl-alpha amino acids
def: Compounds containing an alpha amino acid which bears an acyl group at its terminal nitrogen atom." []

name: N-carbamoyl-alpha amino acids
def: Compounds containing an alpha amino acid which bears an carbamoyl group at its terminal nitrogen atom." []

name: Alpha amino acids
def: Amino acids in which the amino group is attached to the carbon atom immediately adjacent to the carboxylate group (alpha carbon)." []
xrefs: ['Wikipedia:Aromatic_acid']

name: Imidazole carboxylic acids
def: Substituted imidazoles in which the imidazole ring bears a carboxylic acid group." []

name: Indolecarboxylic acids
def: Compounds containing a carboxylic acid group linked to an indole." []

name: Morpholine carboxylic acids
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a morpholine ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups." []

name: Thiomorpholine carboxylic acids
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiomorpholine ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups. Thiomorpholine a six-membered aliphatic ring containing one nitrogen atom and one sulfur atom at positions 1 and 4 respectively, and four carbon atoms." []
synonyms: ['sulfur-containing carboxylic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33576]', 'thiomorpholines" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36393]']

name: Oxirane carboxylic acids
def: Compounds containing an oxirane ring bearing a carboxylic acid group." []

name: Piperazine carboxylic acids
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a piperazine ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups." []

name: Piperidinecarboxylic acids
def: Compounds containing a piperidine ring which bears a carboxylic acid group." []

name: Pyran carboxylic acids
def: Compounds containing a pyran ring which bears a carboxylic acid group." []

name: Pyrazine carboxylic acids
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrazine ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups." []

name: Pyridinecarboxylic acids
def: Compounds containing a pyridine ring bearing a carboxylic acid group." []

name: Pyrimidinecarboxylic acids
def: Pyrimidines with a structure containing a carboxyl group attached to the pyrimidine ring." []

name: Pyrrolidine carboxylic acids
def: Compounds containing a pyrrolidine ring which bears a carboxylic acid. Pyrrolidine is a five-membered saturated aliphatic heterocycle with one nitrogen atom and four carbon atoms." []
synonyms: ['carboxylic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33575]', 'pyrrolidinecarboxylic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:46767]']

name: Pyrroline carboxylic acids
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrroline ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups." []

name: Thiazolecarboxylic acids
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiazole ring which bears a carboxylic acid group." []

name: Thiophene carboxylic acids
def: Compounds containing a thiophene ring which bears a carboxylic acid group." []

name: Triazole carboxylic acids
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a triazole ring substituted by at least one carboxylic acid group." []
synonyms: ['a triazole carboxylic acid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'carboxylic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33575]', 'Triazolecarboxylic Acids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'triazoles" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35727]']

name: Naphthalenecarboxylic acids
def: Compounds containing a naphthalene moiety, which bears a carboxylic acid group one or more positions. Naphthalene is a bicyclic compound that is made up of two fused benzene ring." []
synonyms: ['a naphthoic acid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'naphthoic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25483]', 'Naphthoic acids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Azetidinecarboxylic acids
def: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid group attached to an azetidine ring." []
synonyms: ['azetidinecarboxylic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:46891]', 'carboxylic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33575]']

name: Aziridinecarboxylic acids
def: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid group attached to an aziridine ring." []

name: Anthracenecarboxylic acids
def: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid group attached to an anthracene ring system." []

name: Tellurols
def: Analogues of alcohols and phenols where the oxygen is replaced by a tellurium atom." [DOI:10.1070/RC1999v068n11ABEH000544]
synonyms: ['a tellurol" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organotellurium compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36652]']

name: Tellones
def: Organotellurium compounds with the general formula RC(=Te)R' (R,R\" = organyl)." []

name: Carboselenoic acids and derivatives
def: Organic compounds containing at least one carboselenoyl group, with the formula RC(=O)Se (or a derivative thereof)." []

name: Selenazoles
def: Compounds containing a five-membered aromatic ring with a the carbon atom replaced by a selenium atom (at position 1) and a nitrogen atom (at position 2 or 3)." []

name: Selenoethers
def: Organic compounds containing a selenoether group, with the general formula RseR' ( where R, R' are not H atoms)." []
synonyms: ['a selenoether" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organoselenium compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25712]']

name: Selenoesters
def: Analogues of esters where an oxygen atom is replaced by a selenium atom. They generally have the formula RC(=O)SeR' or RC(=Se)OR'." []
synonyms: ['a selenoester" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organoselenium compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25712]']

name: Telluroethers
def: Organic compounds containing a telluroether group, with the general formula RTeR' ( where R, R' are not H atoms)." []
synonyms: ['a telluroether" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organotellurium compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36652]']

name: Alpha-bromoaldehydes
def: Aldehydes with the general formula C(Br)C(=O)H, with in which the aldehydic C=O function is conjugated to a C-Br group." []

name: Alpha,beta-unsaturated aldehydes
def: Aldehydes of general formula R(1)R(2)C=CR(3)-CH=O or RC#C-CH=O in which the aldehydic C=O function is conjugated to an unsaturated C-C bond at the alpha,beta position." []

name: Alpha-hydrogen aldehydes
def: Aldehydes with the general formula HC(H)(R)C(=O)H, where R is an organyl group." []

name: Beta-hydroxy aldehydes
def: Organic compounds containing an aldehyde substituted with a hydroxy group on the second carbon atom." []

name: Enals
def: An alpha,beta-unsaturated aldehyde of general formula RC=C-CH=O in which the aldehydic C=O function is conjugated to a C=C triple bond at the alpha,beta position." []

name: Ynals
def: An alpha,beta-unsaturated aldehyde of general formula RC#C-CH=O in which the aldehydic C=O function is conjugated to a C#C triple bond at the alpha,beta position." []

name: Terminal alkynes
def: Alkynes featuring a carbon substituent on one acetylenic carbon, and a hydrogen on the other carbon." []

name: Internal alkynes
def: Alkynes featuring carbon substituents on each acetylenic carbon." []

name: Artemisinins
def: Sesquiterpenoids originally isolated from the herb Artemisia annua. Their structure is based on artemisinin, a tetracyclic compound that contains a 1,2-dioxepane fused to an octahydrobenzopyran moiety. The internal peroxide bridge is believed to be a key to the mode of action of artemisinins." [PMID:21155666]
synonyms: ['Artemisinins" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.389.338.055]', 'C15 isoprenoids (sesquiterpenes)" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR0103]', 'sesquiterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26658]']

name: Naphthols and derivatives
def: Naphthalene derivatives carrying one or more hydroxyl (-OH) groups at any ring position." []

name: Nitrosopiperidines
def: Piperidines with a nitroso functional group attached to the piperidine ring." []

name: Nitrosothiols
def: nitroso compounds containing the nitrosothiol group, with the general formula RS=N=O." []
synonyms: ['nitroso compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35800]', 'organic molecular entity" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50860]', 'Organic S-nitroso compounds." RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: N-methylnitrosoureas
def: Organonitrogen compounds with the general formula H3CN(N=O)R(N)=O (R = any atom)." []

name: Peroxycarboxylic acids and derivatives
def: Organic acids with the general formula OOC(R)=O (R = H, organyl group)." []

name: Peroxycarboxylic acids
def: Organic acids with the general formula [H]OOC(R)=O (R = H, organyl group)." []
synonyms: ['a peroxycarboxylic acid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'peroxy acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:52094]', 'Peroxycarboxylates" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Piperidinylpiperazines
def: Heteropolycyclic compounds containing a piperidine ring and a piperazine ring linked together by a single bond that is not part of a ring." []

name: Benzenoids
def: Aromatic compounds containing one or more benzene rings." [ISBN:978-0-08-015659-0]

name: Amines
def: Compounds formally derived from ammonia by replacing one, two or three hydrogen atoms by hydrocarbyl groups, and having the general structures RNH2 (primary amines), R2NH (secondary amines), R3N (tertiary amines)." [ISBN:0967855098]
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Primary amines
def: Amines having the nitrogen atom linked to exactly one hydrocarbyl group." []
synonyms: ['a primary amine" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'primary amine" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:32877]']

name: Secondary amines
def: Amines having the nitrogen atom linked to exactly two hydrocarbyl groups." []

name: Tertiary amines
def: Amines having the nitrogen atom linked to exactly three hydrocarbyl groups." []
synonyms: ['a tertiary amine" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'tertiary amine" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:32876]']

name: Primary aromatic amines
def: Primary amines where the only hydrocarbyl substituent of the amine group is aromatic. Primary amines have the general formula RNH2 (R=aryl)." []
synonyms: ['a primary aromatic amine" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'primary arylamine" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50471]']

name: Tertiary alkylarylamines
def: Tertiary amines where the nitrogen atom is linked to at least one alkyl group and at least one aryl group." []
synonyms: ['a tertiary alkylarylamine" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'tertiary amine" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:32876]']

name: Diarylamines
def: Secondary amines where the two hydrocarbyl substituents of the amine group are aryl groups." []

name: Germacrane sesquiterpenoids
def: Sesquiterpenoids having the germacrane skeleton, with a structure characterized by a cyclodecane ring substituted with an isopropyl and two methyl groups." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['germacrane sesquiterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:68588]', 'germacrane sesquiterpenoid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Germacrane sesquiterpenoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010309]', 'Sesquiterpenoids, Germacrane" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.849.765.787]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:9780412466205 "John Buckingham (1993). Dictionary of Natural Products. Chapman and Hall/CRC; 1 edition (Dec 2 1993)']

name: Triarylamines
def: Organic compounds containing a trialkylamine group, characterized by exactly three aryl groups bonded to the amino nitrogen." []

name: Secondary alkylarylamines
def: Secondary alkylarylamines with the general formula HN(R)R' (R = alkyl, R' = aryl)." []

name: Nitramines
def: Organyl derivatives of nitramide with the general formula RNHO2 (R = organyl group)." []

name: Alkanolamines
def: Organic compounds that carry a hydroxy and an amino functional groups on an alkane backbone." []

name: Nitrile imides
def: Organic compounds with the general structure RC#[N+][N-]R, R[C+]=N=[N-]R, or R[C-]=[N+]=NR." [ISBN:0967855098]
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Imidothioic acids and derivatives

synonyms: ['Imidothioacids and derivatives" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organonitrogen compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35352]', 'organosulfur compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33261]']

name: Diarylethers

name: Hydrazidines

name: Ynols
def: Organooxygen compounds with the general formula R#CO (R = organyl)." []

name: Oxazaphosphinanes

name: 1,2-diols
def: Polyols containing an alcohol group at two adjacent positions." []

name: Organoselenium compounds
def: Organic compounds containing a carbon-selenium bond." []
synonyms: ['Organic Chemicals" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02]', 'organoselenium compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25712]']

name: Organotellurium compounds
def: Compounds containing bond between a carbon atom and a tellurium atom." []
synonyms: ['Organic Chemicals" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02]', 'organotellurium compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36652]']

name: Selenocyanates
def: Organic compounds with the general formula RSeC#N." []
synonyms: ['a selenocyanate" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organoselenium compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25712]']

name: Selenenyl halides

name: Diselenides

name: Selenoxides
def: Organoselenium compounds with the general formula RSe(=O)R' (R,R'= organyl)." []
synonyms: ['a selenoxide" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organoselenium compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25712]']

name: Perselenic acids
def: Compounds containing a P-hydrocarbyl derivative of perselenic acid." []

name: Perselenic acids and derivatives
def: Compounds containing a P-hydrocarbyl derivative of perselenic acid (or a derivative thereof)." []

name: Seleniranes

name: Telluraldehydes
def: Organotellurium compounds with the general formula RC(=Te)H (R =  organyl)." []

name: Ditellurides

name: Tellurones
def: Organotellurium compounds with the general formula R[Te](R')(=O)=O (R,R' = organyl)." []

name: Telluric acids and derivatives

name: Telluric acids
def: Organic acids containing a telluric acid group." []
synonyms: ['a telluric acid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organotellurium compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36652]']

name: Telluroxides
def: Organotellurium compounds R[Te](R')=O (R,R' = organyl)." []
synonyms: ['a telluroxide" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organotellurium compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36652]']

name: Dicarboxdiimides
def: Hydrazine derivatives in which each of the two nitrogen atoms is the central atom of a dicarboximide group." []

name: Carboximidic acids
def: Organic acids with the general formula RC(=N)-OH (R=H, organic group)." []

name: Thiols
def: Organic compounds containing a functional group with the structure RSH (R = organyl)." []
synonyms: ['a mercaptan" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Mercaptans" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Mercapto Compounds" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Sulfhydryl Compounds" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.886.489]', 'thiol" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:29256]', 'thiols" RELATED IUPAC_TERM []']

name: Dioxathiolanes

synonyms: ['organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]', 'oxacycle" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38104]']

name: Organic nitric acids
def: Compounds containing an organonitric acid group." []

name: Oligophosphenes
def: Organophosphorus compounds with the general formula RP=P-PR' (R=alkyl, aryl)." []

name: Diphosphenes
def: Organophosphorus compounds with the general formula RP=PR'(R,R'= alkyl, aryl)." []

name: Azolines
def: Azole derivatives obtained by conversion of one double bond of the azole ring to a single bond." []
xrefs: ['wikipedia:Azole "Wikipedia Article for Azoles']

name: Azolidines
def: Azole derivatives obtained by conversion of both double bonds of the azole ring to single bonds, yielding a saturated ring." []
xrefs: ['wikipedia:Azole "Wikipedia Article for Azoles']

name: O-benzoquinones
def: Benzoquinones where the two C=O groups are attached at the 1- and 2-positions, respectively." []
synonyms: ['benzoquinones" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22729]', 'Benzoquinones" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.806.250]', 'o-quinone" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25622]']

name: M-benzoquinones

name: P-benzoquinones

synonyms: ['benzoquinones" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22729]', 'Benzoquinones" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.806.250]', 'p-quinone" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25830]']

name: Quinones
def: Compounds having a fully conjugated cyclic dione structure, such as that of benzoquinones, derived from aromatic compounds by conversion of an even number of number of -CH= groups into -C(=O)- groups with any necessary rearrangement of double bonds (polycyclic and heterocyclic analogues are included)." [ISBN:0967855098]
synonyms: ['a quinone" RELATED UniProt_TERM []', 'quinone" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36141]', 'quinones" RELATED IUPAC_TERM []', 'Quinones" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.806]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Isoindolines
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a 2,3-dihydro-1H-iso-indole moiety." []

name: Indoles
def: Compounds containing an indole moiety, which consists of pyrrole ring fused to benzene  to form 2,3-benzopyrrole." []

name: Isothiochromenes
def: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing an isothiochromene moiety." []
synonyms: ['2-benzothiopyrans" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organic heterobicyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:27171]', 'organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]']

synonyms: ['1-benzothiopyrans" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a thiochromene" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'thiochromane" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50747]']

name: Alkanes
def: Acyclic branched or unbranched hydrocarbons having the general formula CnH2n+2 , and therefore consisting entirely of hydrogen atoms and saturated carbon atoms." [ISBN:0967855098]
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Alkenes
def: Acyclic branched or unbranched hydrocarbons having one carbon-carbon double bond and the general formula CnH2n." [ISBN:0967855098]

name: Cembranolides
def: Diterpenoids with a structure based on a cembrane skeleton fused to a lactone ring (5- or 6-membered)." []
synonyms: ['cembrane diterpenoid" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:60687]', 'Cembrane diterpenoids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010419]']

name: Hydroxycinnamic acids
def: Compounds containing an cinnamic acid where the benzene ring is hydroxylated." []

name: Cinnamic acids
def: Organic aromatic compounds containing a benzene and a carboxylic acid group forming 3-phenylprop-2-enoic acid." []

name: Coumaric acids
def: Aromatic compounds containing a cinnamic acid moiety hydroxylated at the C2 (ortho-), C3 (meta-), or C4 (para-) carbon atom of the benzene ring." []

name: Isoflavonoids
def: Natural products derived from 3-phenylchromen-4-one." [ISBN:0967855098]
synonyms: ['3-phenylbenzopyrans" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'A polyphenol" BROAD CHEMONT_TERM []', 'isoflavonoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50753]', 'Isoflavonoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1205]', 'Polyphenols" BROAD CHEMONT_TERM []']
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Homoisoflavonoids
def: Naturally occurring oxygen heterocycles with a structure based on a 16-carbon skeleton including a chromanone, chromone or chromane system with a benzyl group at position C-3." [PMID:20583326]
xrefs: ['PMID:20583326 "Qi J et al (2010). New features on the fragmentation patterns of homoisoflavonoids in Ophiopogon japonicus by high-performance liquid chromatography/diode-array detection/electrospray ionization with multi-stage tandem mass spectrometry. Rapid Commun Mass Spectrom.; 24(15):2193-206. doi: 10.1002/rcm.4608.']

name: Homoisoflavans
def: Homoisoflavonoids with a structure based on the chromane system. Chromone is a bicyclic compound consisting of a 3,4-dihydro-1-benzopyran." [PMID:20583326]

name: Cyclitols and derivatives
def: Compounds containing a cycloalkane moiety with one hydroxyl group on each of three or more ring atoms. These of also include derivatives where the hydrogen atom of one or more of the hydroxyl groups is replaced with another atom." []

name: Aminocyclitols and derivatives
def: Cyclitols, or derivatives thereof with at least one hydroxyl group replace by an amino group. These of also include derivatives where the hydrogen atom of one or more of the hydroxyl groups is replaced with another atom." []
synonyms: ['organonitrogen compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35352]', 'organooxygen compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36963]']

name: Inositol phosphates
def: Compounds containing a phosphate group attached to an inositol (or cyclohexanehexol) moiety." []

name: Quinic acids and derivatives
def: Compounds containing a quinic acid moiety (or a derivative thereof), which is a cyclitol made up of a cyclohexane ring that bears four hydroxyl groups at positions 1,3.4, and 5, as well as a carboxylic acid at position 1." []

name: O-galloylquinic acids and derivatives
def: Compounds containing a galloic acid moiety, linked to one hydroxyl group of a quinic acid moiety." []

name: Salicylic acids
def: Ortho-hydroxylated benzoic acids." []
synonyms: ['Benzoates" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.241.223.100]', 'hydroxybenzoic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24676]', 'Salicylates" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.241.223.100.300.595]']

name: Salicylamides
def: Carboxamide derivatives of salicylic acid. Salicylic acid is the ortho-hydroxylated derivative of benzoic acid." []

name: N-piperazineacetamides
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a piperazine ring, which N-substituted with an acetamide group." []

name: Chamigranes
def: Sesquiterpenoids characterized by a 1,1,5,9-tetramethylspiro[5,5]undecane skeleton, formally obtained by linking the C1-C6 and C6-C11 of farnesane together. They are predominantly isolated from algae." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['Chamigrane sesquiterpenoids" EXACT LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010367]', 'Sesquiterpenes" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.849.765]', 'sesquiterpenoid" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26658]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:9780412466205 "John Buckingham (1993). Dictionary of Natural Products. Chapman and Hall/CRC; 1 edition (Dec 2 1993)']

name: Annonaceous acetogenins
def: Waxy derivatives of fatty acids (usually C32 or C34), containing a terminal carboxylic acid combined with a 2-propanol unit at the C-2 position to form a methyl- substituted alpha,beta-unsaturated-gamma-lactone. One of their interesting structural features is a single, adjacent, or nonadjacent tetrahydrofuran (THF) or tetrahydropyran (THP) system with one or two flanking hydroxyl group(s) at the center of a long hydrocarbon chain." [DOI:10.1021/np980406d]
synonyms: ['Acetogenins" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D10.289.054]', 'Annonaceae acetogenins" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK03]', 'polyketide" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26188]']

name: Acylphloroglucinols and derivatives
def: Phloroglucinol derivatives characterized by the presence of a COR group." [DOI:10.1080/08927022.2012.700483]

name: P-toluquinols and derivatives
def: Toluenes with two hydroxyl group attached to the benzene ring in a para-relationship. The hydrogen atom of either hydroxyl group can be substituted by another atom." []

name: P-toluquinols
def: Toluene with two hydroxyl group attached to the benzene ring in a para-relationship." []

name: P-toluquinones
def: Toluene with two ketone group attached to the benzene ring in a para-relationship." []

name: Isoflavanquinones
def: Isoflavans where the phenyl group carries two C=O groups at position 1 and 4, respectively." []

name: Cyclopropanecarboxylic acids and derivatives
def: Organic compounds containing a carboxyl group (or a derivative thereof) attached to a cyclopropane ring." []

name: Cyclopropanecarboxylic acids
def: Organic compounds containing a carboxyl group attached to a cyclopropane ring." []

name: 1-aminocyclopropane-1-carboxylic acids and derivatives
def: Organic compounds containing both a carboxyl group (or a derivative thereof) and an amino group at position C1 of a cyclopropane ring." []

name: 1-aminocyclopropane-1-carboxylic acids
def: Organic compounds containing both a carboxyl group and an amino group at position C1 of a cyclopropane ring." []

name: Halohydrins
def: Alcohols substituted by a halogen atom at a saturated carbon atom otherwise bearing only hydrogen or hydrocarbyl groups (usually used to mean beta-halo alcohols)." [ISBN:0967855098]
synonyms: ['alcohol" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:30879]', 'Haloalcohols" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organohalogen compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36684]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Carbonylimidazoles
def: Substituted imidazoles in which the imidazole ring bears a carbonyl group." []

name: Epoxypiperidines
def: Heteropolycyclic compounds containing an oxirane fused to a piperidine ring." []

name: Thiosulfonimidic o-acids
def: Organic compounds with the general formula HOS(R)(=N)(=S) (R =  alkyl, aryl)." []

name: Thiosulfonimidic s-acids
def: Organic compounds with the general formula HSS(R)(=N)(=O) (R =  alkyl, aryl)." []

name: Trithiosulfonic acids
def: Organic compounds with the general formula HSS(R)(=S)(=S) (R =  alkyl, aryl)." []

name: Sulfinohydroximic acids
def: Organic compounds with the general formula HON=S(R)OH." []

name: Sulfinohydrazonic acids
def: Organic acids with the general formula RS(=NN)OH." []

name: Phenoxides
def: Salts or analogous metal derivatives of phenols." [ISBN:0967855098]
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Isothiocyanate acids
def: Acidic derivatives of isothiocyanates with the general formula RC(=O)N=C=S." []

name: Nitronic acids
def: Organic compounds containing the nitronate functional group with the general formula RC=N+(O)OH or RCN+(=O)OH." []
synonyms: ['Alkylideneazinic acids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Hydrocarbylideneazinic acids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:64709]']

name: Hemiketals
def: Hemiacetals having the structure R2C(OH)OR' ( R' not H ), derived from ketones by formal addition of an alcohol to the carbonyl group." []

name: Dihydroxyphosphanes
def: Organic compounds with the general formula RP(OH)OH." []

name: Carbodithioic acids
def: Organic acids with the general formula RC(=S)SH (R = organyl)." []

name: Benzylethers
def: Aromatic ethers with the general formula ROCR' (R = alkyl, aryl; R'=benzene)." []

name: Dithiosulfonic O-acids
def: Organic acids with the general formula RS(=S)(=S)OH." []
synonyms: ['organic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:64709]', 'organosulfur compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33261]', 'sulfonodithioic O-acid" RELATED IUPAC_TERM []']

name: Dithiosulfonic S-acids
def: Organic acids with the general formula RS(=O)(=S)SH." []
synonyms: ['organic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:64709]', 'organosulfur compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33261]']

name: Coumarinolignans
def: Lignans with a structure characterized by the presence of a 1,4-dioxane bridge substituted by a phenyl group, and fused to a coumarin." [PMID:20556676]
synonyms: ['Coumarolignans" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Lignans" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.140.450]', 'oxacycle" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38104]']
xrefs: ['PMID:20556676 "Begum SA et al (2010). Non-conventional lignans: coumarinolignans, flavonolignans, and stilbenolignans. Fortschr Chem Org Naturst. ;93:1-70.']

name: Diazetidines
def: Organic compounds containing the diazetidine ring, a saturated four-membered ring with two nitrogen atoms and 2 carbon atoms." []

name: Phenylimidazolidines
def: Polycyclic compounds containing an imidazoline substituted by a phenyl group." []

name: Tanshinones, isotanshinones, and derivatives
def: A group of abietane-type norditerpenoid quinones." []
synonyms: ['abietane diterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36762]', 'Abietane diterpenoids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010405]', 'Diterpenes, Abietane" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.426.559.847.723.590]']

name: Tanshinlactones and derivatives
def: Oxasteroids with a structure containing an C-17 steroid skeleton, with two oxygen atoms replacing carbon atoms, and one C=O group. They all have one nitrogen atom at the 15-position. Some tanshinlactones have the second oxygen atom at the 11-position and a C=O group at the 12-position. Others have the second oxygen atom at the 12-position and a C=O group at the 11-position." []

name: Isocopalane and spongiane diterpenoids
def: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the isocopalane  (Tetradecahydro-1,1,4a,7,8,8a-hexamethylphenanthrene) or the 15,16-epoxyisocopalane skeleton." [DOI:10.1016/j.cattod.2014.03.033, DOI:10.2174/157340707780126534]
synonyms: ['diterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23849]', 'Isocopalane and spongiane diterpenoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010411]']

name: Phenylpropanoic acids
def: Compounds with a structure containing a benzene ring conjugated to a propanoic acid." []

name: Quinoline carboxylic acids
def: Quinolines in which the quinoline ring system is substituted by a carboxyl group at one or more positions." []

name: Quinoline carboxamides
def: Quinolines in which the quinoline ring system is substituted by one or more carboxamide groups." []

name: Pyrrole carboxylic acids and derivatives
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrrole ring bearing a carboxyl group (or a derivative thereof)." []

name: Pyrrole carboxylic acids
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrrole ring bearing a carboxyl group." []

name: Pyrrole carboxamides
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrrole ring bearing a carboxamide." []

name: Pyrrole 2-carboxylic acids
def: Pyrrole carboxylic acids where the carboxyl group is attached at position C2." []

name: N-substituted phenoxazines
def: Phenoxyazines where the nitrogen atom is linked to an atom other than the hydrogen atom." []

name: Sulfosalicylic acids and derivatives
def: Salicylic acids (or derivatives thereof) with a sulfate group attached to the benzene ring." []
synonyms: ['benzenesulfonic acids" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:73942]', 'carbonyl compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36586]', 'Salicylates" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.241.223.100.300.595]']

name: Sulfosalicyclic acids
def: Salicylic acids with a sulfate group attached to the benzene ring." []

name: Thiatriazoles
def: Heteroaromatic compounds containing a thiatriazole ring, which is a five-membered aromatic ring with one sulfur atom, three nitrogen atom, and a carbon atom." []
synonyms: ['organonitrogen heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38101]', 'organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]']

name: Aminothiadiazoles
def: Thiadiazoles with an amino group attached to the thiadiazole ring." []
synonyms: ['organonitrogen heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38101]', 'organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]']

name: Methoxypyrazines
def: Pyrazines containing a methoxyl group attached to the pyrazine ring." []

name: Dichlorobenzenes
def: Compounds containing a benzene with exactly two chlorine atoms attached to it." []
xrefs: ['ATDSR:http\\://www.atsdr.cdc.gov/tfacts10.pdf']

name: Benzoic acids
def: Organic Compounds containing a benzene ring which bears at least one carboxyl group." []

name: Isoquinolines and derivatives
def: Aromatic polycyclic compounds containing an isoquinoline moiety, which consists of a benzene ring fused to a pyridine ring and forming benzo[c]pyridine." []

name: Isoquinoline quinones
def: Isoquinoline derivative with a structure containing a 5,8-dihydroisoquinoline-5,8-dione skeleton." []

name: Angular furanocoumarins
def: Furanocoumarins, with a structure characterized by a furan ring angularly fused to a coumarin." []

name: Linear furanocoumarins
def: Furanocoumarins, with a structure characterized by a furan ring linearly fused to a coumarin." []

name: Quinoline quinones
def: Quinoline derivative with a structure containing a 5,8-dihydroisoquinoline-5,8-dione skeleton." []

name: Phenanthraquinones
def: Phenanthrene derivatives containing two ketone groups at position C9 and C10, respectively." []

name: Naphthothiophenes
def: Compounds containing a naphthalene (or a derivative) fused to thiophene." []
synonyms: ['organic heterotricyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26979]', 'organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]']

name: Thienobenzoxepines
def: Compounds containing a benzoxepine fused to a thiophene ring. Thiophene is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one sulfur atom." []
synonyms: ['organic heterotricyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26979]', 'organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]', 'oxacycle" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38104]']

name: Phenyloxazolidines
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing an oxazolidine ring conjugated by a phenyl group." []

name: Phenylisoxazolidines
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing an isoxazolidine conjugated by a phenyl group." []
synonyms: ['organonitrogen heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38101]', 'oxazole" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35790]']

name: 1,2-oxazinanes
def: Compounds containing an oxazinane ring with the nitrogen atom and the oxygen atom at positions 1  and 2, respectively." []

name: Phenylthiomorpholines
def: Compounds containing a thiomorpholine ring conjugated to a phenyl group. Thiomorpholine a six-membered aliphatic ring containing one nitrogen atom and one sulfur atom at positions 1 and 4 respectively, and four carbon atoms." []
synonyms: ['organonitrogen heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38101]', 'organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]']

name: Oxathiazolidines
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing an oxathiazolidine, a saturated five-membered ring having two carbon atoms, one oxygen atom, one nitrogen atom, and one sulfur atom." []
synonyms: ['organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]', 'oxacycle" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38104]']

name: Phenylthiazetidines
def: Compounds containing a thiazetidine ring conjugated to a phenyl group." []
synonyms: ['organonitrogen heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38101]', 'organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]']

name: Isoflavonequinones
def: Isoflavones where the phenyl group carries two C=O groups at position 1 and 4, respectively." [DOI:10.1039/C2CC33204C]
synonyms: ['Isoflavone quinones" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'isoflavones" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38757]', 'Isoflavonoids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1205]']

name: Neoflavans
def: Neoflavonoids with a structure based on a 3,4-dihydro-4-aryl-2H-1-benzopyran skeleton." []

name: Neoflavenes
def: Neoflavonoids with a structure based on a 4-phenylchromene skeleton." []

name: Dalbergiquinols
def: Neoflavonoids with a structure based on a 3,3-diarylprop-1-ene skeleton." []

name: Phenylbenzofurans
def: Organic aromatic compounds that contain a phenyl group attached to a benzofuran moiety. Benzofuran is a bicyclic compound containing a benzene fused to a furan." []

name: O-methylated flavonoids
def: Flavonoids with methoxy groups conjugated to the flavonoid backbone." []
synonyms: ['ether" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25698]', 'flavonoids" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:72544]', 'Flavonoids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK12]', 'Methoxyflavonoids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

synonyms: ['ether" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25698]', 'isoflavonoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50753]', 'Isoflavonoids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1205]']

name: Bromohydrins

name: Fluorohydrins

name: Iodohydrins

name: Alpha-methyldeoxybenzoin flavonoids

name: 2-phenylbenzofurans

name: Tetrahydrofolic acids and derivatives

name: N-benzylalanines

def: Heterocyclic Compounds containing a piperidine ring conjugated to a benzyl group through one nitrogen ring atom." []

name: N-benzylpiperidines
def: Heterocyclic Compounds containing a piperidine ring conjugated to a benzyl group through one nitrogen ring atom." []

name: Thiohydroquinones

name: Aminohydroquinones

name: Phenylsulfates

name: Imidazopiperidines
def: Heterocyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to a piperidine ring. Imidazole is 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms, and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3-positions. Piperidine is a five-membered heterocycle containing five carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom." []

name: 1,2,4-trisubstituted imidazoles

name: 2,4,5-trisubstituted imidazoles

name: Tetrasubstituted imidazoles
def: Imidazoles in which the imidazole ring is substituted at exactly four different positions." []

name: 1,2,4,5-tetrasubstituted imidazoles

name: 2,4-disubstituted oxazoles
def: Compounds containing an oxazole ring substituted at positions 2 and 4 only. Oxazole is a five-membered aromatic heterocycle with one  oxygen, one nitrogen, and three carbon atoms. Isomers include 1,2-oxazole and 1,3-oxazole." []

name: 2,5-disubstituted oxazoles
def: Compounds containing an oxazole ring substituted at positions 2 and 5 only. Oxazole is a five-membered aromatic heterocycle with one  oxygen, one nitrogen, and three carbon atoms. Isomers include 1,2-oxazole and 1,3-oxazole." []

name: 4,5-disubstituted oxazoles
def: Compounds containing an oxazole ring substituted at positions 4 and 5 only. Oxazole is a five-membered aromatic heterocycle with one  oxygen, one nitrogen, and three carbon atoms. Isomers include 1,2-oxazole and 1,3-oxazole." []

name: 2,4,5-trisubstituted oxazoles
def: Compounds containing an oxazole ring substituted at positions 2, 4 and 5 only. Oxazole is a five-membered aromatic heterocycle with one  oxygen, one nitrogen, and three carbon atoms. Isomers include 1,2-oxazole and 1,3-oxazole." []

def: Heterocyclic compounds containing a diazirine ring, which is a three-membered unsaturated cycle with one carbon atom, and two nitrogen atoms joined by a double bond." []

name: Triazirines

name: Triazinanes
def: Compounds containing a triazinane ring, which is a six-membered saturated heterocycle with  three nitrogen ring atoms and three ring carbon atoms." []

name: Molybdopterins
def: Cofactors or analogs thereof, with a structure based on a furan ring fused to a pterin. In addition, the pyran ring features two thiolates, which serve as ligands in molybdo- and tungstoenzymes. In some cases, the alkyl phosphate group is replaced by an alkyl diphosphate nucleotide." [Wikipedia:Molybdopterin]

name: Acyl glucuronides
def: Carbohydrate derivatives containing glucuronic acid linked to another substance through an ester bond attached at position C-1, C-2, C-3, or C-4 of the glucuronic acid moiety. The C-1 acyl glucuronide is usually the initial isomer, However, the acyl group can rearrange from its initial position on the C-1 hydroxyl group of the glucuronic acid moiety to the C-2 and, subsequently, the C-3 and the C-4 hydroxyl group. Formation of the C-3 from the C-2 isomer, and the C-4 from the C-3 isomer is possible, whereas the C-1 isomer cannot result from the other regioisomers via acyl migration." [ISBN:10-1609133455, PMID:12548138]

name: Grayanoids
def: Diterpenoids containing a skeleton based on or derived from the ent-kaurane moiety. Grayanoids usually possess either one of the grayanane, the 2,4-seco-grayanane, the 9,10-seco-grayanane, the 1,5-seco-grayanane, the kalmane, or the leucothane skeleton. It is derived from casbane by 6,10- and 5,14-cyclizations and is a framework of phorbol. The ingenane skeleton is derived by rearrangement of tigliane." def: A group of macrolides with a structure containing a 16-membered lactone ring fused to a 1,7-dioxaspiroundecane ring system and to either a benzofuran (or hydrogenated derivative thereof). name: Thieno[3,4-d]pyridazines
def: Organic heterocyclic compounds consisting of a thieno[3,4-d]pyridazine moiety. Thieno[3,4-d]pyridazine is a bicyclic compound made up of a thiophene ring fused to a pyridazine ring so that the sulfur atom and the two nitrogen atoms are at the 1-, 4-, and 5-position, respectively." []
synonyms: ['organonitrogen heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38101]', 'organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]']

You have full text access to this content Polyfunctionally Substituted Heterocycles: Synthesis of new polyfunctionally substituted phthalazines, thieno [3, 4-d] pyridazines and pyrido [3, 4-c] pyridazines. J. prakt. Chem. 334; 723 -726.']

name: 2-aminothieno[3,4-c]pyridazines
def: Organic compounds containing a thieno[3,4-c]pyridazine that carries an amino group at the 2-position. Thieno[3,4-c]pyridazine is a bicyclic compound made up of a thiophene ring fused to a pyridazine ring so that the sulfur atom and the two nitrogen atoms are at the 1-, 5-, and 6-position, respectively." []
synonyms: ['organonitrogen heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38101]', 'organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]']

name: 2-aminothieno[3,4-d]pyridazines
def: Organic compounds containing a thieno[3,4-d]pyridazine that carries an amino group at the 2-position. Thieno[3,4-d]pyridazine is a bicyclic compound made up of a thiophene ring fused to a pyridazine ring so that the sulfur atom and the two nitrogen atoms are at the 1-, 4-, and 5-position, respectively." []
synonyms: ['organonitrogen heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38101]', 'organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]']

name: N-alkylpiperazines
def: Organic compounds containing a piperazine ring where the nitrogen ring atom carries an alkyl group." []

name: N-methylpiperazines
def: Organic compounds containing a piperazine ring where the nitrogen ring atom carries a methyl group." []

name: N-arylpiperazines
def: Organic compounds containing a piperazine ring where the nitrogen ring atom carries an aryl group." [DOI:10.1016/j.tet.2006.07.011]

name: 30-hydroxysteroids
def: Steroids carrying a hydroxyl group at the 30-position of the steroid backbone." []
synonyms: ['hydroxy steroid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35350]', 'Sterol Lipids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST]']

def: Organic aromatic compounds containing a pyriazinium ring." []

name: 2-aminopyrazinium compounds
def: Organic compounds containing a pyrazinium ring that carries an amine group at the 2-position." []

name: Steroid acids
def: Compounds containing a carboxyl group attached to a steroid backbone." []
synonyms: ['Carboxylated steroids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'steroid acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:47891]', 'Sterol Lipids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST]']

name: Mono-rhamnolipids
def: Rhamnolipids containing exactly one rhamnose sugar ring." [DOI:10.1007/s00253-010-2498-2]

name: Di-rhamnolipids
def: Rhamnolipids containing two rhamnose rings." [DOI:10.1007/s00253-010-2498-2]

name: 3-carboxy-20-oxosteroids
def: Steroid compounds that carry a carboxyl group and a C=O group at the C3- and C20-positions of the steroid backbone, respectively." []

name: 3-carboxy steroids
def: Steroid compounds that carry a carboxyl group at the C3-atom of the steroid backbone." []
synonyms: ['steroid acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:47891]', 'Sterol Lipids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST]']

name: 17-carboxy steroids
def: Steroid compounds that carry a carboxyl group at the C17-atom of the steroid backbone." []
synonyms: ['a 17-carboxy steroid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'steroid acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:47891]', 'Sterol Lipids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:ST]']

name: Azobenzenes
def: Organonitrogen aromatic compounds that contain a central azo group, where each nitrogen atom is conjugated to a benzene ring." [PMID:24502513]
synonyms: ['a diphenyldiazene" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'azobenzenes" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22682]', 'Diphenyldiazenes" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Isodiazenes
def: Organonitrogen compounds with the formula RN(R')N or R[N+](R')N-, where R and R' are organic groups." [ISBN:0967855098]
synonyms: ['a diazanylidene" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'an azamine" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Azamines" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Diazanylidenes" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Hydrazinylidenes" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organonitrogen compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35352]']

name: 1,2-dithiolanes
def: Organic compounds containing a 1,2-dithiolane ring. 1,2-dithiolane moiety is a 5-membered  saturated aliphatic ring with three carbon atoms, and two sulfur atoms at the 1- and 2- ring positions." []

name: 1,3-dithiolanes
def: Organic compounds containing a 1,3-dithiolane ring. 1,3-dithiolane moiety is a 5-membered saturated aliphatic ring with three carbon atoms, and two sulfur atoms at the 1- and 3- ring positions." []

name: 1,2-dithiolane-3-carboxylic acids
def: Organic compounds containing a 1,2-dithiolane ring that bears a carboxylic acid group at the 3-position." []

name: 1,2-dithiolane-4-carboxylic acids
def: Organic compounds containing a 1,2-dithiolane ring that bears a carboxylic acid group at the 4-position." []

name: 1,3-dithiolane-2-carboxylic acids
def: Organic compounds containing a 1,3-dithiolane ring that bears a carboxylic acid group at the 2-position." []

name: 1,3-dithiolane-4-carboxylic acids
def: Organic compounds containing a 1,2-dithiolane ring that bears a carboxylic acid group at the 4-position." []

name: Dithiolanecarboxylic acids
def: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a dithiolane ring that bears one or more carboxylic acids." []

name: 1,2-dithiolanecarboxylic acids
def: Organic compounds containing a 1,2-dithiolane ring that bears one or more carboxylic acid groups. The 1,2-dithiolane moiety is a 5-membered ring with three carbon atoms, and two sulfur atoms at the 1- and 2- ring positions." []
synonyms: ['1,2-dithiolane carboxylic acids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a 1,2-dithiolane carboxylic acid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'a 1,2-dithiolanecarboxylic acid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'carboxylic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33575]', 'dithiolanes" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:39192]']

name: 1,3-dithiolanecarboxylic acids
def: Organic compounds containing a 1,3-dithiolane ring that bears one or more carboxylic acid groups. The 1,3-dithiolane moiety is a 5-membered ring with three carbon atoms, and two sulfur atoms at the 1- and 3- ring positions." []

name: alpha-Mercaptocarboxylic acids
def: Carboxylic acids that bear a thiol group at the C-2 position. Alpha-mercaptocarboxylic acids have the general formula RC(S)C(=O)O, where R = H, organyl group." []
synonyms: ['2-mercaptocarboxylic acids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'sulfur-containing carboxylic acid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33576]']

name: Thiophosphate monoesters
def: Organic compounds containing the thiophosphoric acid functional group or a derivative thereof, with the general structure ROP(OR')(OR'')=S, where exactly one R-group is an organyl group." []
synonyms: ['organic thiophosphate" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37512]', 'phosphorothioic acid monoesters" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Thiophosphate diesters
def: Organic compounds containing the thiophosphoric acid functional group or a derivative thereof, with the general structure ROP(OR')(OR'')=S, where exactly two R-groups are organyl groups." []
synonyms: ['organic thiophosphate" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37512]', 'phosphorothioic acid diesters" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Thiophosphate triesters
def: Organic compounds containing the thiophosphoric acid functional group or a derivative thereof, with the general structure ROP(OR')(OR'')=S, where exactly three R-groups are organyl groups." []
synonyms: ['organic thiophosphate" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37512]', 'phosphorothioic acid triesters" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Organic dithiophosphoric acids and derivatives
def: Organic compounds that contain dithiophosphoric acid or a derivative thereof, with the general formula ROP(S)(=S)OR', (R,R'=H, or organyl group)." []

name: Dithiophosphate S-esters
def: S-ester derivatives of dithiophosphates, with the general structure RSP(O)(O)=S (R = organyl group)." []
synonyms: ['a dithiophosphate S-ester" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organic thiophosphate" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37512]']

name: 1'-(acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho),3'-(acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho)-sn-glycerols
def: Glycerophospholipids in which the O1 and O3 oxygen atoms of the central glycerol moiety are each linked to one 1-monoacylglyerol chain." []

name: Glycerophosphoglycerophosphoglycerols
def: Glycerophospholipids that contain three glycerol moieties sequentially linked to each other with a phosphate group. They include cardiolipins." []

name: Ceramide-1-phosphates
def: Sphingoid analogue of phosphatidic acid formed from ceramide by adding a phosphate group at its 1-position." [Lipidlibrary:aocs.org/Lipids/cer-1-p/index.htm]

name: Phosphonosphingolipids
def: Sphingolipids with a structure based on a sphingoid base that is attached to a phosphonate head group. They differ from Phosphosphingolipids which have a phosphate head group." []

name: Phosphosphingolipids
def: Sphingolipids with a structure based on a sphingoid base that is attached to a phosphate head group. They differ from phosphonospingolipids which have a phosphonate head group." []

name: (2'->5')-dinucleotides
def: Dinucleotides where the two bases are connected via a (2'->5')-phosphodiester linkage." []

name: (3'->5')-dinucleotides
def: Dinucleotides where the two bases are connected via a (3'->5')-phosphodiester linkage." []

name: 5'-phospho-(2'->5')-dinucleotides
def: (2'->5')-dinucleotides in which one of the based bears a phosphate group (or a phosphate chain) at the 5'-position." []

name: 5'-phospho-(3'->5')-dinucleotides
def: (3'->5')-dinucleotides in which one of the based bears a phosphate group (or a phosphate chain) at the 5'-position." []
xrefs: ['PMID:11393397 "Zhu XF and Scott AI (2001). An improved synthesis of the dinucleotides pdCpA and pdCpdA. Nucleosides Nucleotides Nucleic Acids., 20(3):197-211.']

name: Sphenolobane diterpenoids
def: Diterpenoids with a structure characterized by a sphenolobane skeleton. They possess a trans-fused hydroazulenoid skeleton as a common structural motif, but differ in configuration at C(9), where a prenyl group is attached. Sphenolobane is also considered an 'extended' daucane skeleton, with a carbon side chain appended onto the cyclopentane ring." [DOI:10.1016/j.tet.2011.09.022, ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['Diterpenes" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.849.291]', 'diterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23849]', 'Prenyldaucane diterpenoids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Sphenolobane diterpenoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010453]', 'tormesane diterpenes" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']
xrefs: ['ISBN:9780412466205 "John Buckingham (1993). Dictionary of Natural Products. Chapman and Hall/CRC; 1 edition (Dec 2 1993)']

name: Amphilectane, neoamphilectane, cycloamphilectane, and adociane diterpenoids
def: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the amphilectane or a seco-,neo-, or cyclo- derivative thereof. Amphilectane is a tricyclic structure made up of three cyclohexane fused together, with a methyl group at the C11-, C7-, and C3- positions. Additionally, it carries a 2-methylpropyl group at the C1-position. Amphilectanes are presumably derived from serrulatanes. Cycloamphilectanes represent a further cyclisation." [DOI:10.1021/jo952015z, ISBN:3540211241, ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['Amphilectane, cycloamphilectane, adociane and neoamphilectane diterpenoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010441]', 'diterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23849]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:3540211241 "J. Mulzer (2005). Natural Product Synthesis II: Targets, Methods, Concepts. Springer; 2005 edition (Feb. 11 2005)', 'ISBN:9780412466205 "Buckingham J (1993).  Dictionary of Natural Products. Chapman & Hall.1 edition.']

name: Cyclohexane sesterterpenes
def: Sesterterpenoids with a structure containing a cyclohexane linked to an isoprenyl chain. They arise by cyclisation of the acyclic sesterterpene skeleton between carbons 14 and 19." [ISBN:9780412466205]
xrefs: ['ISBN:9780412466205 "John Buckingham (1993). Dictionary of Natural Products. Chapman and Hall/CRC; 1 edition (Dec 2 1993)']

name: Stemarane diterpenoids
def: Diterpenoids with a structure characterized by a stemarane skeleton. Some characteristics include the bicyclic system C/D that is constituted by a bicyclo[3.2.1]octane fused to the bicyclic A/B system in a different fashion with respect to other tetracyclic diterpenes possessing the bicyclo[3.2.1]octane system. Moreover, the two contiguous quaternary carbon atoms,  C(9) and C(10), are present, the former being a spirocyclic atom. Oxygenation can happen at positions C(2), C(7), C(13), C(17), C(18), and C(19)." [http:padis.uniroma1.it/bitstream/10805/2345/8/Tesi_PhD%20corretto.pdf]
synonyms: ['C20 isoprenoids (diterpenes)" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR0104]', 'Diterpenes" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.849.291]', 'diterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23849]']

name: Villanovane, atisane, trachylobane or helvifulvane diterpenoids
def: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the villanovane, atisane, trachylobane or helvifulvane skeleton. The astisane and atisane skeletons arise from the rearrangement of the beyerane cation intermediate. The trachylobane and helvifulvane skeletons are formed by rearrangement of the beyerane cation intermediate followed by cyclisation." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['Diterpenes" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.849.291]', 'diterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23849]', 'Villanovane, atisane, trachylobane and helvifulvane diterpenoids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR010415]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:9780412466205 "John Buckingham (1993). Dictionary of Natural Products. Chapman and Hall/CRC; 1 edition (Dec 2 1993)']

name: Monomethylphosphatidylethanolamines
def: Lipids with a structure containing a glycerol moiety linked at its  terminal C3 atom to a N-methylphosphoethanolamine group, and at its C1 and C2 terminal atoms by an acyl group." [DOI:10.1099/mic.0.26522-0]
synonyms: ['Diacylglycerophosphoethanolamines" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GP0201]', 'phosphatidyl-N-methylethanolamines" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'phosphatidylethanolamine" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:16038]']

name: Dimethylphosphatidylethanolamines
def: Lipids with a structure containing a glycerol moiety linked at its  terminal C3 atom to a N,N-dimethylphosphoethanolamine group, and at its C1 and C2 terminal atoms by an acyl group." [DOI:10.1099/mic.0.26522-0]
synonyms: ['Diacylglycerophosphoethanolamines" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GP0201]', 'phosphatidyl-N-dimethylethanolamines" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'phosphatidylethanolamine" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:16038]']

name: Phosphatidylethanols
def: Glycerophospholipids where the central glycerol is acylated at the 1- and 2-positions by two acyl chains, and is linked at the 3-position to a phosphoethanol.  They are phospholipids formed only in the presence of ethanol via the action of phospholipase D." [PMCID:PMC1233611]
synonyms: ['1,2-diacylglycero-3-phosphoethanols" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'glycerophospholipid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37739]', 'Glycerophospholipids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GP]']

name: 2-arylbenzofuran flavonoids
def: Phenylpropanoids containing the 2-phenylbenzofuran moiety." []

name: 3-arylcoumarin flavonoids
def: Isoflavonoids that bear a ketone group at the C2-position." [DOI:10.1016/j.bmcl.2014.10.033]
synonyms: ['a 3-arylcoumarin flavonoid" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'coumarins" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23403]', 'Isoflavonoids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK1205]']

Synthesis and adenosine receptors binding affinities of a series of 3-arylcoumarins. Journal of Pharmacy and Pharmacology, 65(11), pp 1590-1597.']

name: Peltogynoid flavonoids
def: Flavonoid compounds with a structure based on the isochromeno[4,3-b]-chromene skeleton. This skeleton results from the fusion of an isochromene to a chromene ring system." [DOI:10.1039/P19920000675]
synonyms: ['flavonoids" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:72544]', 'Flavonoids" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PK12]', 'Peltogynoids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Isobenzofurans
def: Organic aromatic compounds containing an isobenzofuran moiety." []

name: Isobenzofuranones
def: Compounds containing a 2-benzofuran moiety that carries an oxo group at the 1 position." []

name: 1-benzopyrans
def: Organic aromatic compounds that 1-benzopyran, a bicyclic compound made up of a benzene ring fused to a pyran, so that the oxygen atom is at the 1-position." []

name: 2-benzopyrans
def: Organic aromatic compounds that 1-benzopyran, a bicyclic compound made up of a benzene ring fused to a pyran, so that the oxygen atom is at the 2-position." []

name: Benzothiopyrans
def: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a pyran ring. Pyran a six-membered heterocyclic, non-aromatic ring, made up of five carbon atoms and one oxygen atom and containing two double bonds." []

name: 1-benzothiopyrans
def: Organic aromatic compounds that 1-benzothiopyran, a bicyclic compound made up of a benzene ring fused to a thiopyran, so that the sulfur atom is at the 1-position." []
synonyms: ['organic heterobicyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:27171]', 'organosulfur heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38106]']

name: 2-benzothiopyrans
def: Organic aromatic compounds that 1-benzothiopyran, a bicyclic compound made up of a benzene ring fused to a thiopyran, so that the sulfur atom is at the 2-position." []

name: Angucyclines
def: Polyketides with a structure based on then benz[a]anthracene skeleton, with the particularity that the central ring of the anthracene moiety is a para-quinone." [DOI:10.1039/C1NP00068C]

name: Methyl esters
def: Organic compounds containing a carboxyl group that is esterified with a methyl group. They have the general structure RC(=O)OR', where R=H or organyl group and R'=methyl group." []

name: Fatty acid methyl esters
def: Compounds containing a fatty acid that is esterified with a methyl group. They have the general structure RC(=O)OR', where R=fatty aliphatic tail or organyl group and R'=methyl group." []
synonyms: ['fatty acid methyl ester" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:4986]', 'Fatty esters" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:FA07]']

name: Dihydrobenzofuran and benzofuran lignans
def: Neolignans in which the two C6-C3 units are linked together by a bond other than Cbeta-Cbeta'. They usually consist of a 1-benzofuran or 2,3-dihydro-1-benzofuran, which is substituted a the 2-, 3-, and 5-positions with a phenyl group, a methyl group, and a propyl group, respectively." [DOI:10.1023/B\:PHYT.0000045495.59732.58]
xrefs: ['DOI:10.1023/B\\:PHYT.0000045495.59732.58 "Kuo-Hsiung Lee, Zhiyan Xiao(2003). Lignans in treatment of cancer and other diseases. Reviews, Volume 2, Issue 3, pp 341-362.']

name: Cyclobutane lignans
def: Lignans with a structure characterized by to phenylpropanoid units coupled together through the C7-C7' and C8-C8' bonds, forming a cyclobutane ring with the C7, C7', C8', and C8 atoms." [DOI:10.1023/B\:PHYT.0000045495.59732.58, DOI:10.5772/28471]
xrefs: ['DOI:10.1023/B\\:PHYT.0000045495.59732.58 "Kuo-Hsiung Lee, Zhiyan Xiao(2003). Lignans in treatment of cancer and other diseases. Reviews, Volume 2, Issue 3, pp 341-362']

name: Alpha-acyloxy ketones
def: Ketones that have an acyloxy substituent alpha to the carbonyl group. They have the general structure R4C(=O)OC(R2)(R3)C(R1)=O (R1=organyl, R4=H or organyl; R2,R3 = any atom)." [PMID:11975534]
synonyms: ['carboxylic ester" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33308]', 'ketone" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:17087]', 'lignan" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25036]']

name: 7,8'-epoxylignans
def: Lignans that contain either isomer of the 7,8'-epoxylignan skeleton. The first isomer consists of a tetrahydrofuran that carries a phenyl group at the 2- and the 4-positions, as well as one a methyl group at the 3- and 5-positions. The second isomer consists of a tetrahydrofuran that carries a benzyl group, a phenyl group, and a methyl group at the 2-, 4-, 5-position, respectively." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['7,8-Epoxytetrahydrofuranoid lignans" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'lignan" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25036]', 'Lignans" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.140.450]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:9780412466205 "John Buckingham (1993). Dictionary of Natural Products. Chapman and Hall/CRC; 1 edition (Dec 2 1993).']

name: 7,9'-epoxylignans
def: Lignans that contain the 7,9'-epoxylignan skeleton, which consists of a tetrahydrofuran that carries a phenyl group, a methyl group, and a benzyl group at the 2-, 3-, 4-position, respectively." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['7,9-Epoxytetrahydrofuranoid lignans" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'lignan" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25036]', 'Lignans" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.140.450]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:9780412466205 "John Buckingham (1993). Dictionary of Natural Products. Chapman and Hall/CRC; 1 edition (Dec 2 1993).']

name: 7,7'-epoxylignans
def: Lignans with a structure based on a 2,5-diaryl-3, 4-dimethyltetrahydrofuran skeleton." [ISBN:9780412466205, PMID:8987506]
synonyms: ['7,7-Epoxytetrahydrofuranoid lignans" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'lignan" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25036]', 'Lignans" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.140.450]']
xrefs: ['ISBN:9780412466205 "John Buckingham (1993). Dictionary of Natural Products. Chapman and Hall/CRC; 1 edition (Dec 2 1993).']

name: 9,9'-epoxylignans
def: Lignans with a structure based on the 9,9'-epoxylignan skeleton, which consists of a tetrahydrofuran that carries two benzyl groups at the 3- and 4-positions. Additionally they are oxygenated at the 2-position to form dibenzylbutyrolactones (oxo group) or a dibenzylbutyrolactols (hydroxyl group)." [ISBN:9780412466205]
synonyms: ['3,4-dibenzyltetrahydrofuran lignans" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', '9,9-Epoxytetrahydrofuranoid lignans" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'lignan" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25036]', 'Lignans" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.140.450]']

name: Stemona alkaloids
def: Alkaloids are characterized by a pyrrolo[1,2- a]azepine nucleus usually linked with two carbon chains mostly forming terminal lactone rings. They can be clasified in different subgroups, based on the different carbon chains attached to C-9 of the pyrroloazepine nucleus." [PMID:10714902, PMID:16491444, PMID:17191845]

name: Croomine-type alkaloids
def: Stemona alkaloids with a structure containing a pyrrolo[1,2-a]azepine group, where the azepine moiety forms a spiro system with oxolane-5-one to give spiro[oxolane-2,9'-pyrrolo[1,2-a]azepine]-5-one. Moreover, another 5-oxooxolane moiety attached to the pyrrole ring." [PMID:16491444]

name: Stichoneurine-type alkaloids
def: Stemona alkaloids with a structure that typically contains a 3-methyloxolan-2-one and a 5-propyloxolan-2-one moieties that are attached to the characteristic pyrrolo[1,2-a]azepine skeleton at the C3 and C9 position, respectively." [PMID:16491444]
synonyms: ['alkaloid" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22315]', 'Stichoneurines" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Tuberostemonine-type alkaloids" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Protostemonine-type alkaloids
def: Stemona alkaloids with a structure containing a pyrrolo[1,2-a]azepine skeleton (S1) , one 5-oxooxolane moiety (S2), and one a 5-(oxolan-2-yl)oxolan-2-one moiety (S3). The S2 moiety is linked to the C3 atom of the pyrrole ring in the S1 moiety. Additionally, the azepine ring of S1 is fused to one oxolane ring of the S3 moiety." [PMID:16491444]

name: Valparane and mulinane diterpenoids
def: Diterpenoids with a structure based on either the valparane or mulinane skeleton. Valparane and mulinane are tricyclic compounds containing a tetradecahydrocyclohepta[e]indene skeleton. Valparane carries a 1-methylethyl at the 3-position, as well as three methyl groups at the 5a-, 8-, and 10b-position of the ring system. Mulinane carries a 1-methylethyl at the 3-position, as well as three methyl groups at the 3a-, 5a-, and 8-position of the ring system." [ISBN:9780412466205]

name: Elisabethane diterpenoids
def: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the elisabethane skeleton, a tricyclic serrulatane derivative that is formed by connecting the C1 and C9 atom of serrulatane. This class of compounds also includes seco-elisabethane derivatives, nor-elisabethanes (resulting from the loss of one carbon atom), and bisnor-elisabethanes (resulting from the loss of two carbon atoms)." [ISBN:3540211241]
synonyms: ['C20 isoprenoids (diterpenes)" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR0104]', 'Diterpenes" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.849.291]', 'diterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23849]']

name: Elisapterane, elisabane, cumbiane or colombiane diterpenoids
def: Diterpenoids with a structure based on either the elisapterane, elisabane, cumbiane or colombiane skeleton. They derive from serrulatane. Elisapterane is a tetracyclic compound formed by C10-C15 cyclization of elisabethane. Elisabane (nor-elisapterane) results from the loss of the C17 carbon atom of elisapterane. Cumbiane is formed by C10-C16 cyclization of the elisabethane carbon skeleton. Meanwhile, the cleavage of the C15-C16 bond of cumbiane yields the seco-cumbiane skeleton. Colombiane is also a tetracyclic skeleton arises from the C12-C2 cyclization of the elisabethane skeleton." [ISBN:3540211241]
synonyms: ['C20 isoprenoids (diterpenes)" BROAD LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR0104]', 'Diterpenes" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.849.291]', 'diterpenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23849]']

name: Ileabethane, pseudopterane or nor-sandresane diterpenoids
def: Diterpenoids with a structure based on either the ileabethane, the pseudopterane, or the nor-sandresane skeleton. Ileabethane is a tricyclic carbon skeleton arising from the C8-C14 of serrulatane. In the nor-sandresane skeleton, a cyclohexane ring is fused to a seven-membered saturated aliphatic carbocycle, which could stem from the rearrangement of an amphilectane-based precursor involving loss of a carbon atom and a 1,2-alkyl shift with ring expansion." [ISBN:0849382165, ISBN:3540211241]

name: Organic 1,3-dipolar compounds
def: Electrically neutral organic molecules carrying a positive and a negative charge in one of their major canonical descriptions. In most dipolar compounds the charges are delocalized; however the term is also applied to species where this is not the case. The term 1,3-dipolar compounds is used for those in which a significant canonical resonance form can be represented by a separation of charge over three atoms (in connection with 1,3-dipolar cycloadditions)." [ISBN:0967855098]

name: Inorganic 1,3-dipolar compounds
def: Electrically neutral inorganic molecules carrying a positive and a negative charge in one of their major canonical descriptions. In most dipolar compounds the charges are delocalized; however the term is also applied to species where this is not the case. The term 1,3-dipolar compounds is used for those in which a significant canonical resonance form can be represented by a separation of charge over three atoms (in connection with 1,3-dipolar cycloadditions)." [ISBN:0967855098]
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Gelsemium alkaloids
def: Alkaloids with a structure that is based on the tetracyclic gelsemium skeleton. These alkaloids contain an oxindole function and a cage-like, hydroaromatic residue which is believed to arise from an intermediate related to anhydrovobasinediol by formation of a 6,20 bond and rearrangement to an oxindole. The major alkaloids in this group are related to Gelsemine; however, a smaller group, characterized by Gelsedine, lack the 6,20 bond, and have also lost C-21." [ISBN:978-1-4200-7769-8]

name: (3'->5')-cyclic dinucleotides and analogues
def: Cyclic compounds consisting of two ribose moieties connected by two 5',3'-phosphodiester bonds to form a cycle. Each ribose unit is N-linked to a nucleic base or an analogue thereof. Some natural (3'->5')-cyclic dinucleotides include c-di-AMP. Synthetic derivatives are generally more elaborated molecules in which one or the two nucleobase moieties, and/or sugar residues, and/or phosphodiester linkers have been modified." [PMCID:PMC3991150, PMID:23767818]

def: Glycerophosphoglycerophosphates that contain exactly two fatty acyl chains attached to the glycerol moiety, one through an ester linkage at the O2-position, and the other through an ether linkage at the O1-position." []

name: 1-(1Z-alkenyl),2-acylglycerophosphoglycerophosphates
def: Glycerophosphoglycerophosphates that carry exactly one acyl chain attached to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage at the O2-position,  and one 1Z-alkenyl chain attached through an ether linkage at the O1-position." []

name: 1-alkyl,2-acylglycerophosphoinositols
def: Glycerophosphoinositols that contain exactly two fatty acyl chains attached to the glycerol moiety, one through an ester linkage at the O2-position, and the other through an ether linkage at the O1-position." []
synonyms: ['1-alkyl,2-acylglycerophosphoinositols" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:GP0602]', 'alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:68522]', 'glycerophosphoinositol" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36315]']

name: 1-(1Z-alkenyl),2-acylglycerophosphoinositols
def: Glycerophosphoinositols that carry exactly one acyl chain attached to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage at the O2-position,  and one 1Z-alkenyl chain attached through an ether linkage at the O1-position." []

name: Dialkylglycerophosphoinositols
def: Glycerophosphoinositols that contain exactly two fatty acyl chains attached to the glycerol moiety, one through ether linkages at the O1- and O2-positions." []

name: Monoalkylglycerophosphoinositols
def: Glycerophosphoinositols that contain exactly on fatty acyl chain attached to the glycerol moiety through an ether linkage." []

name: 1-(1Z-alkenyl)glycerophosphoinositols
def: Glycerophosphoinositols that carry exactly one 1Z-alkenyl chain attached to the glycerol moiety through an ether linkage." []

name: Glycero-3-phosphosulfocholines
def: Lipids containing a glycerol moiety carrying a phosphosulfocholine at the 3-position." []

name: Dolichols
def: A group of long-chain mostly unsaturated organic compounds that are made up of varying numbers of isoprene units terminating in an alpha-saturated isoprenoid group, containing an alcohol functional group. The three isoprene units at the distal end  are trans-linked." [ASIN:B00A9YH6LS, Wikipedia:wiki/Dolichol]
xrefs: ['ASIN:B00A9YH6LS "Bach TJ and Rohmer M (2012). Isoprenoid Synthesis in Plants and Microorganisms: New Concepts and Experimental Approaches. Springer New York; 1 edition (Sept. 19 2012).']

name: Dolichyl monophosphates
def: Polyprenyl compounds consisting of a monophosphate group substituted by a dolichyl moiety." []
synonyms: ['Dolichol monophosphates" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR0308]', 'Dolichol Phosphates" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.033.415.230.250]', 'dolichyl phosphate" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:16214]']

name: Dolichyl diphosphates
def: Polyprenyl compounds consisting of a diphosphate group substituted by a dolichyl moiety." []
synonyms: ['Dolichol diphosphates" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR0309]', 'dolichyl diphosphate" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:15750]']

name: Acyldolichols
def: Polyprenyl compounds consisting of a dolichyl moiety carrying an acyl group." []

name: Bactoprenols
def: Compounds consisting of a (un-) substituted bactoprenyl group, which is a C-55 isoprenoid alcohol obtained by condensation of 10 unsaturated isoprene units a one saturated isoprene unit." [PMCID:PMC1264965]
synonyms: ['Bactoprenols" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:PR0301]', 'isoprenoid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24913]', 'polyprenol" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26199]']
xrefs: ['ASIN:B00A9YH6LS "Bach TJ and Rohmer M (2012). Isoprenoid Synthesis in Plants and Microorganisms: New Concepts and Experimental Approaches. Springer New York; 1 edition (Sept. 19 2012).']

name: Bactoprenol monophosphates
def: Polyprenyl compounds consisting of a monophosphate group substituted by a bactoprenyl moiety." []

name: Bactoprenol diphosphates
def: Polyprenyl compounds consisting of a diphosphate group substituted by a bactoprenyl moiety." []

name: Fatty acyl glycosides of mono- and disaccharides
def: Compounds composed of a mono- or disaccharide moiety linked to one hydroxyl group of a fatty alcohol or of a phosphorylated alcohol (phosphoprenols), a hydroxy fatty acid or to one carboxyl group of a fatty acid (ester linkage) or to an amino alcohol." [Cyberlipid:glycolip/glyl0006.htm]
synonyms: ['Fatty acyl glycosides of mono- and disaccharides" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:FA1301]', 'glycoside" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24400]', 'lipid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:18059]', 'O-acyl carbohydrate" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:52782]']

name: Dialkylthioethers
def: Organosulfur compounds containing a thioether group that is substituted by two alkyl groups." []

name: Alkylarylthioethers
def: Organosulfur compounds containing a thioether group that is substituted by an alkyl and an aryl group." []

name: Diarylthioethers
def: Organosulfur compounds containing a thioether group that is substituted by two aryl groups." []

name: Organic salts
def: Organic compounds consisting of an assembly of cations and anions." [ISBN:0967855098]
synonyms: ['an organic salt" BROAD []', 'organic salt" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24868]']
