name: Inorganic salts
def: Inorganic compounds consisting of an assembly of cations and anions." [ISBN:0967855098]
xrefs: ['ISBN:0967855098 "IUPAC. Compendium of Chemical Terminology, 2nd ed. (the \'Gold Book\'). Compiled by A. D. McNaught and A. Wilkinson. Blackwell Scientific Publications, Oxford (1997).']

name: Trialkylsilanes
def: Organosilicon compounds containing exactly one alkyl chain attached to the silicon atom." []
synonyms: ['organic molecular entity" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50860]', 'Organosilicon Compounds" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.715]']

name: Phosphoric monoester monoamides
def: Organophosphorus compounds containing a monoamide derivative of a phosphoric acid monoester functional group. They have the general structure R1OP(=O)(OH)N(R3)R4, where R1 = organyl group and R3-R4 = H or organyl." []
synonyms: ['organic molecular entity" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50860]', 'organooxygen compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36963]']

name: Phosphoric diester monoamides
def: Organophosphorus compounds containing a monoamide derivative of a phosphoric acid diester functional group. They have the general structure R1OP(=O)(OR2)N(R3)R4, where R1-R2 = organyl group and R3-R4 = H or organyl." []

name: Phosphoric monoester diamides
def: Organophosphorus compounds containing a monoamide derivative of a phosphoric acid diester functional group. They have the general structure R1OP(=O)(N(R2)R3)N(R4)R5, where R1 = organyl group and R2-R5 = H or organyl." []
synonyms: ['organic molecular entity" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50860]', 'organooxygen compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36963]']

name: Organic phosphoric acid triamides
def: Organophosphorus compounds with the general formula RNP(R2)(R3)=O (R=alkyl, aryl; R2-R3 = amine groups)." []

name: Carbothioic S-esters
def: Ester derivatives of carbothioic S-acids, with the general structure RSC(=O)R' where R = organyl group and R' = H or organyl group." []

name: Carbothioic S-lactones
def: Cyclic organosulfur compounds with the general structure RC(=O)SR', R-R' = organyl group, where the central atom is part of the ring." []

name: Carbothioic O-esters
def: Ester derivatives of carbothioic O-acids, with the general structure ROC(=S)R' where R = organyl group and R' = H or organyl group." []

name: Carbothioic O-lactones
def: Cyclic organosulfur compounds with the general structure RC(=S)OR', R-R' = organyl group, where the central atom is part of the ring." []

name: Carbothioic halides
def: Organosulfur compounds with the general structure RC(=S)X, where R = organyl group and X = halogen atom." []
synonyms: ['organohalogen compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36684]', 'organosulfur compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33261]']

name: Carbodithioic acid esters
def: Ester derivatives of a carbodithioic acid (RC(=S)SH)." []

name: Carbodithiolactones
def: Cyclic organosulfur compounds with the general formula RC(=S)SR', where the central carbon atom is part of a ring; R,R' = organyl group." []

name: Oxime esters
def: Organic compounds containing an ester derivative of the oxime functional group." []
xrefs: ['PMCID:PMC2843764 "Bachovchin DA et al (2010). Oxime esters as selective, covalent inhibitors of the serine hydrolase retinoblastoma-binding protein 9 (RBBP9). Bioorg Med Chem Lett.; 20(7): 2254‚Äì2258.']

name: Hydroxamic acid esters
def: Hydroxamic acids in which the hydrogen of the hydroxy group has been replaced by an organyl group." []

name: Cyclic carboximidic acids
def: Organic acids with the general formula RC(=N)-OH (R=H, organic group), where the carboximidic acid group is part of a cycle." []

name: Imidolactones
def: Cyclic organooxygen compounds with the general structure R(=N)OR' where the central carbon atom is part of a ring, and R,R' = organyl group." []
synonyms: ['imidate" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:52479]', 'organonitrogen compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35352]', 'oxacycle" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38104]']

name: Imidothioic acids
def: Sulfur derivatives of imidic acid containing the functional group -RC(=N)S, obtained by replacing the oxygen atom by a sulfur atom." []

name: Cyclic imidothioic acids
def: Organic compounds containing the imidothioic acid group as part of a cycle." []
synonyms: ['cyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33595]', 'organonitrogen compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35352]']

name: Imidothiolactones
def: Analogs of imidolactones where the oxygen atom is replaced by a sulfur atom. They have the general structure RC(=N)SR' where the central carbon atom is part of a ring. R,R' =  organyl group." []
synonyms: ['heterocyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:5686]', 'organonitrogen compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35352]', 'organosulfur compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33261]']

name: Imidolactams
def: Cyclic organooxygen compounds containing the structure RC(=N)N where the central carbon atom and one of the linked nitrogen atoms are part of the same ring( R here is an organyl group). They can also be viewed as analogs of lactams where the oxygen atom is replaced by a nitrogen atom." []

name: Cyclic imidoyl halides
def: Imidoyl halides with the general formula R(X)C=NR' (R, R'=H, alkyl, aryl), where the central carbon atom is part of a ring." []
synonyms: ['cyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33595]', 'organosulfur compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33261]']

name: Vinylogous halides
def: Organic compounds containing a halogen atom, which is indirectly attached to a carbonyl via an intervening vinyl (>C=C<) moiety." []

name: Vinylogous acids
def: Organic compounds containing a hydroxyl group, which is indirectly attached to a carbonyl via an intervening vinyl (>C=C<) moiety." [Wikipedia:en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vinylogy]

name: Vinylogous amides
def: Organic compounds containing an amine group, which is indirectly attached to a carbonyl via an intervening vinyl (>C=C<) moiety." []

name: Vinylogous esters
def: Organic compounds containing an ester group, which is indirectly attached to a carbonyl via an intervening vinyl (>C=C<) moiety." []

name: Organic phosphonic acid diamides
def: Organophosphorus compounds containing a diamide derivative of phosphonic acid, with the general structure R1P(=O)(N(R2)R3)N(R4)R5, where R = organyl and R2-R5 = H or organyl group." []

name: Phosphonic acid diesters
def: Organophosphorus compounds containing a diester derivative of phosphonic acid, with the general structure ROP(=O)OR' (R,R' = organyl group)." []

name: Phosphonic amide esters
def: Organophosphorus compounds containing a diester derivative of phosphonic acid amide, with the general structure ROP(=O)N(R')R\" (R = organyl group, R'-R\" = H or organyl group)." []

name: Ketene silyl acetals
def: Organosilicon compounds with the general structure OC(O[Si])=CR, where R = H or organyl group." []
synonyms: ['organoselenium compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25712]', 'Organosilicon Compounds" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.715]']

name: Silyl monohalides
def: Organosilicon compounds with the general formula  RSi(R')(R'')X; R-R'' = organyl group, X = halogen atom." []
synonyms: ['organosilicon compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25713]', 'Organosilicon Compounds" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.715]']

name: Silyl dihalides
def: Organosilicon compounds with the general formula  RSi(R')(X)X; R-R' = organyl group, X = halogen atom." []
synonyms: ['organosilicon compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25713]', 'Organosilicon Compounds" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.715]']

name: Silyl trihalides
def: Organosilicon compounds with the general formula  RSi(X)(X)X; R = organyl group, X = halogen atom." []
synonyms: ['organosilicon compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25713]', 'Organosilicon Compounds" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.715]']

name: Aralkylamines
def: Alkylamines in which the alkyl group is substituted at one carbon atom by an aromatic hydrocarbyl group." []

name: N-acetoxyarylamines
def: Arylamines that contain an acetytoxy group attached to the nitrogen." []

name: Dialkylarylamines
def: Aliphatic aromatic amines in which the amino group is linked to two aliphatic chains and one aromatic group." []
synonyms: ['dialkylarylamine" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:23665]', 'tertiary amino compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50996]']

name: Alkyldiarylamines
def: Tertiary alkylarylamines having two aryl and one alkyl groups attached to the amino group." []
synonyms: ['an alkyldiarylamine" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'aromatic amine" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33860]', 'N-alkyldiarylamines" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'tertiary amino compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50996]']

name: Haloalkenes
def: Compounds derived from an alkene by replacing a hydrogen atom with a halogen atom." []

name: Bromoalkenes
def: Compounds derived from an alkene by replacing a hydrogen atom with a bromine atom." []

name: Chloroalkenes
def: Compounds derived from an alkene by replacing a hydrogen atom with a chlorine atom." []

name: Fluoroalkenes
def: Compounds derived from an alkene by replacing a hydrogen atom with a fluorine atom." []
synonyms: ['<new synonym>" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'organofluorine compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37143]']
xrefs: ['PMID:612451 "Clayton JW. (1977). Toxicology of the fluoroalkenes: review and research needs. Environ Health Perspect.;21:255-67.']

name: Iodoalkenes
def: Compounds derived from an alkene by replacing a hydrogen atom with an iodine atom." []

name: Fatty N-acylethanolamines
def: Lipids containing an fatty acyl chain attached to a N-acyl ethanolamine group." []

name: Fatty Acyls
def: Organic molecules synthesized by chain elongation of an acetyl-CoA primer with malonyl-CoA (or methylmalonyl-CoA) groups that might contain a cyclic functionality and/or are substituted with heteroatoms." []
synonyms: ['Fatty Acyls" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:FA]', 'lipid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:18059]', 'organooxygen compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36963]']
xrefs: ['HTTP:www.premierbiosoft.com/tech_notes/lipidomics.html']

name: 2-aroylquinolines
def: Compounds containing a quinoline which carries an aroyl group at the 2-position. An aroyl group is a univalent radical R-CO- derived from an aromatic carboxylic acid." [Wikipedia:en.wiktionary.org/wiki/aroyl]

name: 5-amino-2-aroylquinolines
def: Compounds containing a quinoline which carries an aroyl group at the 2-position, and an amino group at the 5-position." []
xrefs: ['PMID:20148562 "Nien CY et al (2010). 5-Amino-2-aroylquinolines as highly potent tubulin polymerization inhibitors. J Med Chem., 53(5):2309-13.']

name: 4-aroylquinolines
def: Compounds containing a quinoline which carries an aroyl group at the 4-position. An aroyl group is a univalent radical R-CO- derived from an aromatic carboxylic acid." [Wikipedia:en.wiktionary.org/wiki/aroyl]

name: Stenine-type alkaloids
def: Alkaloids which can be structurally represented by the tetracyclic\nfuro[2,3-h]pyrrolo[3,2,1-jk][1]benzazepin-10(2H)-one nucleus." [PMID:10714902, PMID:16491444]
xrefs: ['PMID:10714902 "Pilli RA e al (2000). Recent progress in the chemistry of the Stemona alkaloids. Nat. Prod. Rep., 17, pp 117‚Äì127.', 'PMID:16491444 "Greger H. (2006). Structural relationships, distribution and biological activities of stemona alkaloids. Planta Med., 72(2), pp 99-113']

name: Stemoamide-type alkaloids
def: Alkaloids which include a tricyclic 2H-furo[3,2-c]pyrrolo[1,2-a]azepine nucleus." []
synonyms: ['alkaloid" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22315]', 'organic heterotricyclic compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26979]']

name: Stemonamine-type alkaloids
def: Alkaloids with a structure characterized by the tetracyclic 2AH,11H-spiro[1H-cyclopenta-[b]pyrrolo[1,2-a]azepine-11,2A-furan]-5A,10-dione nucleus with a spirolactone ring at C-12." [PMID:10714902]
xrefs: ['PMID:10714902 "Pilli RA e al (2000). Recent progress in the chemistry of the Stemona alkaloids. Nat. Prod. Rep., 17, pp 117‚Äì127.']

name: Tuberostemospironine-type alkaloids
def: Alkaloids with a structure that is characterized by a 2H-spiro[furan-2,9A[9H]pyrrolo[1,2-a]azepin]-\n5-one nucleus which displays a spiro gamma-lactone at C-9 of the basic ring." [PMID:10714902]
xrefs: ['PMID:10714902 "Pilli RA e al (2000). Recent progress in the chemistry of the Stemona alkaloids. Nat. Prod. Rep., 17, pp 117‚Äì127.']

name: Parvistemoline-type alkaloids
def: Alkaloids that feature a conserved pyrrolo[1,2-a]azepine nucleus. They are characterized by a hexahydro-2,6-dimethyl-5-oxofuro[3,2-b]furan-3-yl moiety attached to C-9 in the pyrrolo[1,2-a]azepine nucleus." [PMID:10714902]
xrefs: ['PMID:10714902 "Pilli RA e al (2000). Recent progress in the chemistry of the Stemona alkaloids. Nat. Prod. Rep., 17, pp 117‚Äì127.']

name: Saccharolipids
def: Compounds in which fatty acids are linked directly to a sugar backbone, forming structures that are compatible with membrane bilayers. In the saccharolipids, a sugar substitutes for the glycerol backbone that is present in glycerolipids and glycerophospholipids. The most familiar saccharolipids contain an acylated glucosamine. In contrast to others glycolipids, the fatty acid is not glycosidically linked to the sugar moiety." [PMID:15722563]
synonyms: ['lipid" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:18059]', 'lipopolysaccharide" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:16412]', 'Saccharolipids" RELATED LIPIDMAPS_TERM [LIPIDMAPS:SL]']
xrefs: ['PMID:15722563 "Fahy E. et al (2005). A comprehensive classification system for lipids. J Lipid Res;46(5), pp 839-61.']

name: Acetate salts
def: Organic compounds containing acetic acid as its acid component." []

name: Hydrobromides
def: Organic salts that results from the reaction of hydrobromic acid with an organic base." []

name: Hydrochlorides
def: Organic salts that results from the reaction of hydrochloric acid with an organic base." [Wikipedia:http\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hydrochloride]

name: Acetamides
def: Organic compounds with the general formula RNHC(=O)CH3, where R= organyl group." []

name: Phenylalkylamines
def: Organic amines where the amine group is secondary and linked on one end to a phenyl group and on the other end, to an alkyl group." []

name: Alkylglucosinolates
def: Organic compounds containing a glucosinolate moiety that carries an alkyl chain." []

name: Beta-diketones
def: Organic compounds containing two keto groups separated by a single carbon atom." []

name: Organic potassium salts
def: Organic compounds containing a potassium ion." []

name: Organic sodium salts
def: Organic compounds containing a sodium ion." []

name: Organic sulfate salts
def: Organic compounds containing a sulfate ion." []
synonyms: ['organic molecular entity" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50860]', 'sulfate salt" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35175]']

name: Organic bromide salts
def: Organic compounds containing a bromine ion." []

name: Organic chloride salts
def: Organic compounds containing a chlorine ion." []

name: Organic iodide salts
def: Organic compounds containing a iodine ion." []
synonyms: ['organic iodide salt" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50356]', 'organic salt" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24868]']

name: Organic perchlorate salts
def: Organic compounds containing a perchlorate ion." []

name: Dithiocarbamic acids and derivatives
def: Organosulfur compounds with the general formula SC(=S)N(R1)R2; R1-R2 =  H or organyl group." []

name: Dithiocarbamic acids
def: Organosulfur compounds with the general formula HSC(=S)N(R1)R2; R1-R2 =  H or organyl group." []

name: Dithiocarbamic acid esters
def: Organosulfur compounds with the general formula R3SC(=S)N(R1)R2; R1-R2 =  H or organyl group, R3 = organyl." []

name: Cyclic dithiocarbamates
def: Organic compounds containing the dithiocarbamic acid group as part of a cycle." []
xrefs: ['DOI:10.1007/s10593-006-0106-2 "Trofimova TP et al (2006). Rearrangement of cyclic dithiocarbamates. Chem Heterocycl Compd, 42(3),419-421.']

name: Phosphine sulfides
def: Compounds having the general formula R3P=S <=> R3P+S-." []

name: Phosphine imides
def: Organophosphorus compounds with the general formula R1P(R2)(R3)N=R4; R1 = organyl, R2-R4 = H or organyl." []

name: Organic oxides
def: Organic compounds containing an oxide group." []

name: Inorganic arsenides
def: Inorganic compounds containing arsenic with one or more less electronegative elements." []

name: Inorganic sulfides
def: Inorganic compounds of sulfur with a less electronegative element." []
synonyms: ['inorganic molecular entity" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24835]', 'sulfide" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26822]']

name: Inorganic phosphides
def: Inorganic compounds containing phosphorus with a less electronegative element or elements." []

name: Inorganic oxides
def: Inorganic chemical compounds with one or more oxygen atoms combined with another element." []

name: Inorganic hydrides
def: Inorganic compounds in which hydrogen is bonded to a more electropositive element or group. Usually, they contain one or more hydrogen centers having nucleophilic, reducing, or basic properties." [Wikipedia:en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hydride]

name: Inorganic selenides
def: Inorganic chemical compounds in which selenium serves as an anion with oxidation number of -2. The selenium atom here when participating in a chemical bond, is linked to a less electronegative atom." [Wikipedia:http\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Selenide]

name: Nitrosamides
def: Organonitrogen compounds with the general formula O=CN(R)-N=O, where R=H or organyl group." []

name: Inorganic nitrosamines
def: Inorganic compounds containing the nitrosamine functional group, with the structure R2NN=O." []

name: Inorganic hydroxylamines
def: Inorganic compounds containing the hydroxylamine group RN(R')-OH, where R,R' = H or inorganic moiety." []

name: Isporenylated bicyclo [2.2.2] alkaloids
def: Alkaloids characterized by the unique bicyclo [2.2.2] ring system, constituted mainly from tryptophan, proline, or substituted  proline derivatives, where the olefinic unit of the isoprene moiety is usually oxidatively cyclized across the alpha carbon of a cyclic dipeptide (a piperazinedione)." [ISBN-13:978-3540665731]
xrefs: ['ISBN-13:978-3540665731 "Leeper FJ and Vederas JC (2000). Biosynthesis: Aromatic Polyketides, Isoprenoids, Alkaloids, Volume 209; pp 98-99.']

name: Dialkyl peroxides
def: Organic compounds containing a peroxide group substituted by two alkyl groups." []

name: 2-aminoanthraquinones
def: Organic compounds containing an anthraquinone ring system, which is substituted at the 2-position by an amino group." []

name: 8-hydroxyquinolines
def: Compounds containing a quinoline moiety, which carries a hydroxy group at the 8-position. Quinoline consists of a benzene ring fused to a pyrimidine ring to form benzo[b]azabenzene." [PMCID:PMC3793592]

name: Polybrominated biphenyls
def: Organic aromatic compounds containing a biphenyl moiety, which is substituted at two or more ring positions by a bromine atom." []
synonyms: ['a polybrominated biphenyl" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'biphenyls" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22888]', 'organochlorine compound" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36683]', 'PBBs" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Benzidines
def: Organic compounds containing the benzidine skeleton, made up of a biphenyl ring system substituted at the 4- and 4'-positions with a unsubstituted amine group." []
synonyms: ['aromatic amine" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33860]', 'Benzidines" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.185.100]', 'biphenyls" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22888]']

name: 3,3'-disubstituted benzidines
def: Organic compounds containing a benzidine skeleton, which is substituted only at the 3-  and 3'-positions." []

name: 3,3'-dihalogenated benzidines
def: Organic compounds containing a benzidine skeleton, which is substituted at different positions, only two of which (3- and 3'-) carry a halogen atom." []

[DOI:10.1007/978-3-642-22144-6_18]

Phenanthridone-type alkaloids have the highest oxygenated C ring in all Amaryllidaceae alkaloids, and they always show an amide group in ring B. On the contrary, alkaloids of the phenanthridine type often show completely aromatic ring system, occasionally with a methylation quaternary nitrogen atom." [DOI:10.1007/978-3-642-22144-6_18]

name: 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleoside phosphorothioates
def: 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleoside phosphate analogues, where a phosphate oxygen has been exchanged for sulphur generating a chiral phosphorothioate. In 3',5'-cyclic nucleoside phosphorothioate, the oxygen atoms at the 3'- and 5'-positions of the ribose are part of the phosphorothioate group." []
synonyms: ['organic phosphorothioate anion" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:74950]', 'purines" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26401]']

name: 3',5'-cyclic pyrimidine nucleoside phosphorothioates
def: 3',5'-cyclic pyrimidine nucleoside phosphate analogues, where a phosphate oxygen has been exchanged for sulphur generating a chiral phosphorothioate. In 3',5'-cyclic nucleoside phosphorothioate, the oxygen atoms at the 3'- and 5'-positions of the ribose are part of the phosphorothioate group." []
synonyms: ['organic phosphorothioate anion" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:74950]', 'pyrimidines" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:39447]']

name: 2',3'-dideoxy-3'-thionucleosides
def: 2',3'-deoxyribonucleosides, where the ribose unit is thio-substituted at the 3'-position. The nucleobases here are limited to purine, pyrimidine, and pyridine derivatives." []

name: 2',3'-dideoxy-3'-thionucleoside triphosphates
def: 2',3'-deoxyribonucleoside derivatives, where the ribose unit is thio-substituted at the 3'-position, and at the 5'-position by a triphosphate group. The nucleobases here are limited to purine, pyrimidine, and pyridine derivatives." []
xrefs: ['PMID:17319676 "Meena et al. (2008). 2\',3\'-Dideoxy-3\'-thionucleoside triphosphates: syntheses and polymerase substrate activities. Org Lett., 9(6), pp 1161-1163.']

name: 2',3'-dideoxy-3'-thionucleoside diphosphates
def: 2',3'-deoxyribonucleoside derivatives, where the ribose unit is thio-substituted at the 3'-position, and at the 5'-position by a diphosphate group. The nucleobases here are limited to purine, pyrimidine, and pyridine derivatives." []

name: 2',3'-dideoxy-3'-thionucleoside monophosphates
def: 2',3'-deoxyribonucleoside derivatives, where the ribose unit is thio-substituted at the 3'-position, and at the 5'-position by a monophosphate group. The nucleobases here are limited to purine, pyrimidine, and pyridine derivatives." []

name: 5'-deoxyribonucleosides
def: Nucleosides in which the oxygen atom at the 5'position of the ribose moiety has been replaced by another atom. The nucleobases here are limited to purine, pyrimidine, and pyridine derivatives." []

name: 5'-deoxy-5'-thionucleosides

name: Organic cyanides

name: Dinitrophenols

name: N-acetylarylamines

synonyms: ['sulfone" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35850]', 'Thiirane-1, 1-diones" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'triglyceride" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:17855]']

name: Methoxylated amphetamines
def: Compounds containing an amphetamine moiety, where the benzene ring is O-methylated." []
synonyms: ['Methoxylated phenylisopropylamines" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'amphetamines" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35338]', 'o-Methylated amphetamines" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'o-Methylated phenylisopropylamines" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Sulfonated stilbenes
def: Stilbenes that carry a sulfone group at one or more positions of either benzene rings." []
synonyms: ['Stilbenes" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.455.426.559.389.150.700]', 'stilbenoid" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:26776]', 'sulfone" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35850]']

name: N-acylimidazoles
def: Compounds containing an imidazole ring, which is N-substituted by an acyl group." []

name: Methylcarbamates
def: Methyl esters of carbamic acid." []

name: Diazanaphthalenes
def: Aromatic heterocyclic chemical compounds containing a naphthalene derivative, where two carbon atoms are replaced by nitrogen atoms. They are subdivided in benzodiazines and naphthyridines." []

name: Benzodiazines
def: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a diazine ring. The diazine ring is an analogue of benzene, where two carbon atoms are replaced by nitrogen atoms." []

name: Thiuram monosulfides
def: Organic disulfides that have the general structural formula RN(R')C(=S)SCC(=S)N(R\")R\"', where R-R\"'=alkyl groups." []

name: Thiuram disulfides
def: Organic disulfides that have the general structural formula RN(R')C(=S)SSC(=S)N(R\")R\"', where R-R\"'=alkyl groups." []
synonyms: ['Disulfides" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D01.248.497.158.874.390]', 'organosulfur compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33261]', 'tertiary amine" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:32876]']

name: Furanonaphthodioxoles
def: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a 1,3-dioxole ring linearly fused to the a naphthofuran." []

name: Dithiophosphate S,S-diesters
def: Organic compound containing a S,S-diester derivative of dithiophosphoric acid." []

name: Chloronaphthalenes
def: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a naphthalene moiety substituted at one or more positions by a chlorine atom." []

name: CDP-ethanolamines
def: Phosphoethanolamines that consist of an ethanolamine having a cytidine 5'-diphosphate moiety attached to the oxygen." []

name: Phenylisopropylamines
def: Organic aromatic compounds containing a 1-phenylpropan-2-amine moiety." []

name: Methoxyphenylisopropylamines
def: Organic aromatic compounds containing a 1-phenylpropan-2-amine substituted at one or more ring position with a methoxy group." []
synonyms: ['a methoxyphenylisopropylamine" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Methoxylated phenylisopropylamines" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'phenylalkylamine" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:60977]']

name: 1,3-oxazolobenzo-1,4-diazepines
def: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a 1,3-oxazole ring fused to the 1,-4-diazepine moiety of a 1,4-benzodiazepine ring system." []

name: 2',5'-dideoxyribonucleosides
def: Nucleosides characterized by a purine or pyrimidine base, which is N-linked to a 2',5'-dideoxyribose moiety." []

name: 5'-S-alkylthio-5'-deoxyribonucleosides
def: A 5'-deoxyribonucleoside where  the 5'-hydroxy group of the sugar moiety is substituted by a methylsulfanyl group." []

name: 5'-azido-5'-deoxyribonucleosides
def: A 5'-deoxyribonucleoside where the 5'-hydroxy group of the sugar moiety is substituted by a methylsulfanyl group." [DOI:10.3390/molecules19022434]

name: 2-benzylaminopyridines
def: Aromatic compounds containing pyridine ring substituted at the 2-position by a benzylamine group." []
synonyms: ['aminopyridine" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38207]', 'aralkylamine" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:18000]', 'Benzylamines" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.092.200]']

name: Organic dichromates
def: Organic compounds containing a dichromate moiety." []
synonyms: ['chromium oxoanion" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35402]', 'organic molecular entity" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50860]']

name: Benzotropolones
def: Organic aromatic polycyclic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a tropolone." []

name: Furoic acid esters
def: Ester derivatives of furoic acid." []
synonyms: ['carboxylic ester" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33308]', 'furans" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24129]', 'Furoate esters" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []']

name: Alkoxides
def: Organooxygen compounds with the general structure RO-, where R is an alkyl group." []

name: Methoxides
def: Compounds containing a methoxide group with the formula H3CO-." []

name: Alpha-haloketones
def: Organic compounds contaning a halogen atom attached to the alpha carbon atom relative to C=O group." []

name: Alpha-chloroketones
def: Organic compounds contaning a chlorine atom attached to the alpha carbon atom relative to C=O group." []

name: Indole-3-carbinol and derivatives
def: Compounds containing an indole ring system, which is substituted at the 3-position with a methanol." []
synonyms: ['indole-3-methanol and derivatives" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'indolyl alcohol" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:38467]']

name: 2,5-disubstituted morpholines
def: Organic compounds containing a morpholine ring, which is substituted at the 2- and 5-positions." []

name: Acenaphthylenes
def: Aromatic polycyclic compounds containing an acenaphthylene moiety. Acenaphthylene is a carbotricyclic compound, consisting of a naphthalene with positions C1 and C8 connected by an ethylene bridge." []

name: Ecdysteroids
def: Polyhydroxylated oxosteroids possessing a cyclopentano-perhydro-phenantrene with beta side-chain at C-17, which is the product of terpene biosynthesis through mevalonic acid, cholesterol and related sterols. Ecdysteroids are found in certain plants and animals." [PMID:15638733]

name: Punaglandins and related compounds
def: Cyclopentadienone and cyclopentenone prostaglandins, which are chlorinated at the endocyclic R-carbon position." []

name: Fluoromethoxy benzamides
def: Organic compounds containing a benzamide, which is substituted by a fluoromethoxy group." []
synonyms: ['benzamides" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:22702]', 'Benzamides" BROAD MeSH_TERM [MESH:D02.065.277]', 'organofluorine compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37143]']

name: N'-substituted-N,N'-diacylhydrazines
def: Hydrazine derivatives where the hydrazine group is N-acylated at both nitrogen atoms, only one of which is substituted." []
synonyms: ['carbohydrazide" RELATED [CHEBI:35363]', 'organonitrogen compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35352]', 'organooxygen compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36963]']

name: 2-heteroaryl carboxamides
def: Compounds containing a heteroaromatic ring that carries a carboxamide group." []
synonyms: ['carboxamide" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:37622]', 'organic aromatic compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:33659]']

name: B-type proanthocyanidins
def: Proanthocyanidins, which are characterized by the presence of two or more flavonoid units linked to each other only by either one 4->6, one 4->8, or one 8->8 CC-bond." [DOI:10.1039/b101061l, PMID:12430722, PMID:26386288]

name: Inorganic chromium trioxides
def: Inorganic compounds containing a chromium trioxide moiety." []
synonyms: ['chromium oxide" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:48235]', 'inorganic molecular entity" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:24835]']

name: Organic chromium trioxides
def: Organic compounds containing a chromium trioxide moiety." []
synonyms: ['chromium oxide" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:48235]', 'organic molecular entity" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:50860]']

name: C8-prenylated coumarins
def: Aromatic compounds containing a coumarin skeleton, which is substituted by a prenyl group at the C8-position." []

name: 4-hydroxy-6,7-benzomorphans
def: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a 6,7-benzomorphan skeleton, which is hydroxylated at the ring 4-position." []

name: 2,6-dimethyl-3-benzazocines
def: Aromatic compounds containing a 6,7-benzomorphan skeleton, which is substituted by methyl group at the 2- and 6-positions." []

name: 4-azaandrostanes
def: Azasteroids that are characterized by an androstane skeleton, where the carbon atom at the 4-position has been replaced by a nitrogen atom." []

name: Pyridinolates
def: Aromatic compounds similar to phenoxide, with the difference that one carbo atom of the benzene ring is replaced by a nitrogen compound." []

name: Selenenic acids
def: Aromatic compounds containing a moiety of the generic structure RSeOH, where R is an organic group." []
synonyms: ['organoselenium compound" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25712]', 'oxygen molecular entity" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25806]']

name: 1,2,4-triazolo[3,4-a]phthalazines
def: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a 1,2,4-triazole fused to and sharing a nitrogen atom with the diazine ring of a phthalazine moiety." [PMID:24313754]
synonyms: ['a 1,2,4-triazolo[3,4-a]phthalazine" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'Phthalazines" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:36597]', 'triazoles" BROAD ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:35727]']

name: A-type proanthocyanidins
def: Proanthocyanidins, which are characterized by the presence of two or more flavonoid units linked to each other by both a 2->7 and a 4->b (or 4->8) interflavonoid CC-bonds." [DOI:10.1039/b101061l, PMID:12430722]

name: C-type proanthocyanidins
def: Proanthocyanidins, which are characterized by the presence of three or more flavonoid units linked to each other by exactly 4->8 interflavonoid CC-bonds." [ISBN:9780123849533, PMID:21141823]

name: Dipeptides
def: Organic compounds containing a sequence of exactly two alpha-amino acids joined by a peptide bond." []

name: Oligopeptides
def: Organic compounds containing a sequence of between three and ten alpha-amino acids joined by peptide bonds." []
synonyms: ['alpha-oligopeptides" RELATED CHEMONT_TERM []', 'oligopeptide" RELATED ChEBI_TERM [CHEBI:25676]', 'Oligopeptides" RELATED MeSH_TERM [MESH:D12.644.456]']

name: Chemical entities
def: Constitutionally or isotopically distinct atoms, molecules, ions, ion pairs, radicals, radical ions, complexes, conformers etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity." []
